ical-polarization-mechanism-2022-10%5C%22%3Emade%20us%20more%20polarized%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Broadly%20speaking%2C%20social%20media's%20always-on%20nature%20is%20unnatural.%20We%20aren't%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theatlantic.com%2Ftechnology%2Farchive%2F2021%2F10%2Ffix-facebook-making-it-more-like-google%2F620456%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esupposed%20to%20talk%20so%20much%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20posting%20in%20front%20of%20thousands%20of%20people%20every%20day%20causes%20our%20ability%20to%20communicate%20to%20break%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20for%20all%20its%20flaws%2C%20I%20have%20depended%20on%20big%20platforms.%20My%20job%20as%20a%20freelance%20journalist%20hinges%20on%20a%20public%20audience%20and%20my%20ability%20to%20keep%20tabs%20on%20developing%20news.%20The%20fatigue%20I%20have%20felt%20is%20therefore%20partly%20fueled%20by%20another%2C%20more-pressing%20concern%3A%20Which%20social%20network%20should%20I%20bank%20on%3F%20It%20isn't%20that%20I%20don't%20want%20to%20post%3B%20I%20just%20don't%20know%20where%20to%20do%20it%20anymore.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3EIt%20isn't%20that%20I%20don't%20want%20to%20post%3B%20I%20just%20don't%20know%20where%20to%20do%20it%20anymore.%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20past%20year%2C%20I've%20helplessly%20migrated%20alongside%20most%20of%20my%20network%20from%20one%20new%20platform%20to%20another%20%E2%80%94%20Discord%2C%20Bluesky%2C%20Threads.%20You%20name%20it%2C%20I've%20tried%20it.%20The%20pattern%20is%20the%20same%3A%20I%20sign%20up%20for%20the%20hot%2C%20new%20app%2C%20toy%20with%20it%20for%20a%20few%20days%2C%20and%20then%20quickly%20abandon%20it.%20While%20widespread%20platform%20migrations%20have%20taken%20place%20successfully%20over%20the%20years%20%E2%80%94%20I%20migrated%20from%20Google's%20Orkut%2C%20a%20popular%20platform%20in%20India%20and%20Brazil%20in%20the%20late%20aughts%2C%20to%20Facebook%20to%20Instagram%20to%20TikTok%20%E2%80%94%20I%20have%20never%20before%20found%20myself%20in%20no%20man's%20land.%20If%20none%20of%20these%20platforms%20are%20lining%20up%20to%20be%20the%20new%20Facebook%2C%20what%20%3Cem%3Eis%3C%2Fem%3E%20the%20future%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChand%20Rajendra-Nicolucci%2C%20who%20researches%20digital%20public%20infrastructure%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Michigan%2C%20said%20there's%20a%20reboot%20taking%20place%20now%20and%20that%20social%20media's%20future%20might%20be%20%26quot%3Bmore%20private%20and%20more%20fragmented.%26quot%3B%20In%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpublicinfrastructure.org%2F2023%2F03%2F29%2Fthe-three-legged-stool%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewhite%20paper%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20earlier%20this%20year%2C%20he%20and%20his%20colleagues%20envisioned%20a%20%26quot%3Bpluriverse%26quot%3B%20consisting%20of%20existing%20platforms%20and%20an%20ecosystem%20of%20%26quot%3Bvery%20small%20online%20platforms%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20private%20communities%20and%20niche%20services%20that%20host%20the%20kind%20of%20intimate%20or%20interest-specific%20conversations%20poorly%20served%20by%20today's%20digital%20public%20sphere.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20way%2C%20the%20pluriverse%20is%20already%20here.%20People%20can%20be%20active%20on%20half%20a%20dozen%20social-media%20apps%2C%20using%20each%20for%20a%20unique%20purpose%20and%20audience.%20On%20%26quot%3Bpublic%26quot%3B%20platforms%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-linkedin-got-weird-work-life-blurred-lines-of-oversharing-2023-9%5C%22%3ELinkedIn%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-killed-twitter-irrelevant-meta-threads-debt-mark-zuckerberg-2023-7%5C%22%3EX%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20formerly%20Twitter%2C%20I%20carefully%20curate%20my%20presence%20and%20use%20them%20exclusively%20as%20public-broadcasting%20tools%20for%20promotions%20and%20outreach.%20But%20for%20socializing%2C%20I%20retreat%20to%20various%20tight-knit%2C%20private%20groups%20such%20as%20iMessage%20threads%20and%20Instagram's%20Close%20Friends%20list%2C%20where%20I%20can%20be%20more%20spontaneous%20and%20personal%20in%20what%20I%20say.%20But%20while%20this%20setup%20is%20working%20OK%20for%20now%2C%20it's%20a%20patchwork%20solution.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EOnline%20towns%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENo%20matter%20how%20fun%20group%20chats%20and%20breakout%20social%20apps%20such%20as%20BeReal%20are%2C%20I've%20missed%20the%20borderless%20experience%20that%20large%20platforms%20offer%20%E2%80%94%20a%20place%20where%20I%20can%20discover%20viral%20content%2C%20expand%20my%20network%2C%20and%20participate%20in%20global%20conversations.%20Rebecca%20Rinkevich%2C%20the%20director%20of%20the%20Institute%20for%20Rebooting%20Social%20Media%2C%20doesn't%20expect%20giant%20social%20platforms%20to%20die%20anytime%20soon%20%E2%80%94%20or%20ever%20%E2%80%94%20since%20their%20accessible%20reach%20has%20played%20a%20pivotal%20role%20in%20everything%20from%20tracking%20natural%20crises%20to%20activism.%20But%20as%20people's%20attention%20splinters%20across%20dozens%20of%20platforms%2C%20she%20believes%20%26quot%3Bthe%20government%20and%20the%20public%20will%20have%20to%20work%20harder%20to%20engage%20in%20dialogue%20online%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMike%20McCue%2C%20Flipboard's%20CEO%2C%20believes%20that%20the%20next%20big%2C%20social%20platform%20must%20bring%20together%20the%20benefits%20of%20both%20worlds%2C%20he%20said%3A%20%26quot%3Bthe%20quality%20and%20trust%20in%20small%2C%20transparent%20communities%20with%20the%20ability%20for%20those%20quality%20conversations%20to%20reach%20millions.%26quot%3B%20But%20instead%20of%20one%20platform%20that%20manages%20to%20appease%20everyone%2C%20the%20future%20of%20social%20media%20is%20looking%20more%20like%20a%20network%20of%20platforms%20that%20offer%20people%20a%20customized%20experience.%20The%20ideal%20system%20would%20not%20only%20allow%20you%20to%20migrate%20to%20new%20social%20apps%20without%20losing%20your%20network%20or%20profile%20but%20also%20link%20them%20together%20so%20that%20you%20could%20post%20on%20one%20and%20a%20friend%20could%20comment%20on%20it%20from%20another.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3EThe%20future%20of%20social%20media%20is%20looking%20more%20like%20a%20network%20of%20platforms%20that%20offer%20people%20a%20customized%20experience.%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3ETake%20Threads%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20Meta's%20attempt%20to%20build%20a%20Twitter%20replacement.%20It%20runs%20on%20the%20ActivityPub%20protocol%2C%20which%20means%20that%20Threads'%20more%20than%20100%20million%20users%20will%20eventually%20be%20able%20to%20interact%20with%20Mastodon%2C%20an%20open-source%20social%20platform%20that%20uses%20the%20same%20coding%20system%2C%20without%20ever%20signing%20up%20for%20it.%20Similarly%2C%20on%20Mastodon%2C%20people%20can%20build%20their%20own%20private%2C%20little%20communities%2C%20while%20still%20having%20the%20option%20to%20break%20out%20and%20share%20their%20content%20with%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20platform's%20over%2010%20million%20users.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThink%20of%20it%20like%20a%20town.%20Maybe%20your%20home%20(account)%20is%20in%20the%20Threads%20or%20Mastodon%20neighborhood.%20You%20spend%20a%20lot%20of%20time%20in%20the%20privacy%20of%20your%20home%20talking%20to%20close%20friends%20in%20group%20chats%20and%20private%20lists%2C%20but%20you%20also%20stroll%20about%20to%20see%20what's%20happening%20in%20your%20neighborhood%20%E2%80%94%20a%20limited%20group%20of%20people%20you%20enjoy%20spending%20time%20around%20online.%20Sometimes%2C%20you%20venture%20out%20to%20the%20global%20town%20square%20to%20hear%20what%20people%20in%20different%20communities%20around%20the%20world%20are%20talking%20about.%20Sometimes%20you%20even%20contribute%20to%20the%20conversation%20or%20hang%20up%20posters%20to%20promote%20your%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20kind%20of%20open%2C%20decentralized%20system%20would%20help%20break%20down%20big%20platforms'%20walled%20gardens%2C%20whose%20one-size-fits-all%20approach%20has%20had%20vastly%20detrimental%20effects.%20Instead%20of%20living%20in%20Facebook%20city%20under%20Facebook's%20laws%2C%20the%20decentralized%20approach%20offers%20everyone%20more%20control%20over%20the%20social-media%20experience%20and%20allows%20people%20to%20pick%20the%20communities%20and%20feeds%20they're%20most%20interested%20and%20comfortable%20in.%20Though%20none%20of%20these%20platforms%20have%20tried%20to%20make%20money%20yet%2C%20there%20are%20a%20variety%20of%20business%20paths%3A%20Like%20Threads%2C%20platforms%20could%20turn%20to%20in-app%20ads%2C%20or%20like%20Mastodon%2C%20platforms%20could%20turn%20to%20grants%2C%20donations%2C%20and%20sponsorships.%20Since%20the%20business%20model%20shapes%20how%20the%20platform%20works%2C%20people%20would%20be%20free%20to%20set%20up%20shop%20on%20the%20platforms%20they%20prefer.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20spent%20the%20past%20few%20months%20on%20Mastodon%20and%20Bluesky%2C%20a%20Jack%20Dorsey-backed%20decentralized%20social%20network%2C%20and%20have%20found%20them%20the%20best%20bets%20so%20far%20to%20replace%20Twitter.%20Their%20clutter-free%20platforms%20already%20match%20the%20quality%20of%20discourse%20that%20was%20on%20Twitter%2C%20albeit%20not%20at%20the%20same%20scale.%20And%20that's%20the%20only%20problem%20with%20these%20platforms%3A%20They%20aren't%20compatible%20with%20each%20other%20or%20big%20enough%20on%20their%20own%20to%20replace%20today's%20giants.%20While%20there%20are%20efforts%20to%20bridge%20them%20and%20allow%20users%20to%20interact%20across%20the%20platforms%2C%20none%20have%20proved%20successful.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20these%20and%20other%20decentralized%20platforms%20find%20a%20way%20to%20merge%20into%20a%20larger%20ecosystem%2C%20they%20will%20force%20big%20platforms%20to%20change%20their%20tune%20in%20order%20to%20keep%20up.%20And%20hopefully%2C%20that%20future%20will%20yield%20a%20more%20balanced%20and%20regulated%20online%20lifestyle.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20healthier%20internet%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20its%20best%2C%20Steve%20Teixeira%2C%20the%20chief%20product%20officer%20at%20Mozilla%2C%20said%20that%20social%20media%20facilitated%20connection%2C%20regardless%20of%20geographic%20or%20temporal%20boundaries%2C%20and%20helps%20people%20stay%20informed%2C%20encounter%20novel%20ideas%2C%20and%20access%20vital%20services.%20At%20the%20moment%2C%20though%2C%20%26quot%3Bit%20isn't%20doing%20any%20of%20these%20things%20particularly%20well%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20The%20problem%20is%20that%20social%20media%20is%20trying%20to%20do%20too%20many%20things%20at%20once.%20Splintered%20social%20media%20would%20let%20each%20of%20the%20internet's%20key%20functions%20thrive%20in%20its%20own%20context%20%E2%80%94%20you%20could%20stay%20in%20touch%20with%20family%20members%20and%20keep%20up%20with%20your%20political%20representatives%20without%20your%20private%20memories%20getting%20wedged%20in%20between%20political%20drama.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3EInstead%20of%20living%20in%20Facebook%20city%20under%20Facebook's%20laws%2C%20the%20decentralized%20approach%20offers%20everyone%20more%20control%20over%20the%20social-media%20experience.%3C%2Fq%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20problem%20is%20that%20users%20have%20very%20little%20control%20over%20what%20they%20experience%20online.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.apa.org%2Fmonitor%2F2022%2F11%2Fstrain-media-overload%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EStudies%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20found%20that%20news%20overload%20from%20social%20media%20can%20cause%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftime.com%2F5125894%2Fis-reading-news-bad-for-you%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estress%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20anxiety%2C%20fatigue%2C%20and%20lack%20of%20sleep.%20By%20democratizing%20social%20media%2C%20users%20can%20turn%20those%20negative%20health%20effects%20around%20by%20taking%20more%20control%20over%20who%20they're%20associated%20with%2C%20what%20they%20look%20at%20in%20their%20feeds%2C%20and%20how%20algorithms%20are%20influencing%20their%20social%20experience.%20And%20by%20splintering%20our%20time%20across%20a%20variety%20of%20platforms%20%E2%80%94%20each%20with%20a%20different%20approach%20to%20content%20moderation%20%E2%80%94%20the%20online%20communication%20ecosystem%20ends%20up%20better%20reflecting%20the%20diversity%20of%20the%20people%20who%20use%20it.%20People%20who%20wish%20to%20keep%20their%20data%20to%20themselves%20can%20live%20inside%20tight-knit%20circles.%20Those%20who%20don't%20want%20a%20round-the-clock%20avalanche%20of%20polarizing%20content%20can%20change%20what%20their%20feed%20shows%20them.%20Activists%20looking%20to%20spread%20a%20message%20can%20still%20reach%20millions.%20The%20list%20goes%20on.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BInstead%20of%20policymakers%20and%20users%20having%20to%20plead%2C%20poke%2C%20and%20prod%20platforms%20to%20change%2C%26quot%3B%20Rajendra-Nicolucci%20said%2C%20%26quot%3Bdecentralization%20would%20enable%20them%20to%20take%20matters%20into%20their%20own%20hands%2C%20allowing%20many%20different%20answers%20to%20the%20question%3A%20'How%20should%20platform%20X%20work%20to%20coexist%3F'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETailoring%20social%20media%20to%20people's%20needs%20could%20revolutionize%20how%20we%20spend%20time%20online.%20Swapping%20out%20virality-incentivized%20algorithms%20in%20favor%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbridging.systems%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eones%20that%20resonate%20with%20diverse%20audiences%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20for%20example%2C%20can%20reduce%20bias%20and%20polarization.%20And%20experts%20have%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fpii%2FS2772503022000159%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efound%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20a%20collection%20of%20networks%20would%20%26quot%3Boptimize%20itself%20solely%20for%20public%20good%2C%26quot%3B%20rather%20than%20fall%20into%20the%20pitfalls%20of%20traditional%20platforms%20%E2%80%94%20an%20unhealthy%20obsession%20with%20metrics%20and%20meaningless%20interactions.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20hard%20to%20predict%20the%20future%2C%20least%20of%20all%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20online%20services%20where%20new%20apps%20can%20go%20viral%20%E2%80%94%20and%20then%20fail%20%E2%80%94%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fwhat-is-bereal-app-how-does-it-work-2022-4%5C%22%3Eflash%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20but%20the%20breakup%20of%20monolithic%20social-media%20platforms%20and%20the%20rise%20of%20myriad%20new%20social%20experiences%20has%20felt%20like%20an%20urgent%2C%20long-overdue%20turn%20of%20events.%20It%20has%20propelled%20millions%2C%20including%20me%2C%20to%20question%20the%20status%20quo%20%E2%80%94%20did%20I%20need%20to%20add%20a%20dozen%20hashtags%20in%20hopes%20of%20making%20my%20sunset%20picture%20go%20viral%3F%20%E2%80%94%20and%20embrace%20a%20healthier%20relationship%20with%20social%20media.%20No%20one%20knows%20what%20the%20next%20major%20social%20platform%20will%20look%20like.%20But%20until%20it%20emerges%2C%20I%20expect%20to%20continue%20living%20a%20splintered%20and%20nomadic%20online%20social%20life.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Chr%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20data-mrf-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fshubham-agarwal%5C%22%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-uri%3D%5C%22d6d846ef1e7d832abbabfa4f3180a7dc%5C%22%20data-analytics-module%3D%5C%22body_link%5C%22%20data-analytics-post-depth%3D%5C%22100%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fauthor%2Fshubham-agarwal%5C%22%20data-analytics-product-module%3D%5C%22body_link%5C%22%3EShubham%20Agarwal%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0is%20a%20freelance%20technology%20journalist%20from%20Ahmedabad%2C%20India%20whose%