e%20Disney%20Dream%20cruise%20ship.%3Cp%3EGianna%20Alexis%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%20%3Cli%3EGianna%20Alexis%20worked%20for%20Disney%20Cruise%20Lines%20on%20the%20Disney%20Dream%20ship%20when%20she%20was%2024.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EShe%20quit%20after%20just%20four%20months%20because%20of%20burnout%20and%20long%20working%20hours.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EAlexis%20said%20she%20had%20to%20work%20at%20least%2070%20hours%20a%20week%20and%20was%20paid%20less%20than%20minimum%20wage.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Gianna%20Alexis%2C%20a%20former%20crew%20member%20of%20Disney%20Cruise%20Line.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20three%20years%20old%20when%20I%20sailed%20on%20my%20first%20Disney%20cruise%2C%20and%20I%20thought%20it%20was%20the%20coolest%20thing.%20It%20was%20the%20best%20vacation%20ever%2C%20so%20I%20went%20every%20few%20years%20after%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20always%20been%20excited%20about%20working%20for%20Disney%2C%20so%20I%20applied%20for%20a%20job%20at%20Disney%20Cruise%20Line%20in%202017.%20When%20I%20found%20out%20I%20got%20the%20job%2C%20I%20was%20so%20excited%20I%20cried.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20work%20started%2C%20Disney%20took%20us%20through%20a%20training%20that%20was%20designed%20to%20get%20us%20excited%20about%20the%20work.%20On%20the%20last%20day%20of%20training%2C%20we%20were%20told%20to%20get%20ready%20at%204%20a.m.%20Then%2C%20the%20company%20had%20a%20sniffing%20dog%20to%20smell%20our%20suitcases%2C%20which%20I%20didn't%20expect%20at%20all%20%E2%80%94%20it%20all%20seemed%20so%20different%20because%20the%20only%20experience%20I%20had%20embarking%20on%20a%20cruise%20ship%20was%20from%20a%20guest's%20point%20of%20view.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20first%20hired%20as%20a%20merchandise%20person%20to%20work%20in%20the%20shops%2C%20then%20the%20company%20moved%20me%20to%20the%20Bibbidi%20Bobbidi%20Boutique%2C%20which%20was%20a%20total%20dream%20of%20mine.%20This%20boutique%20is%20the%20place%20where%20kids%20between%20three%20and%2012%20get%20makeovers%20%E2%80%94%20we%20do%20their%20hair%2C%20makeup%2C%20and%20nails.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20lot%20of%20girls%20that%20I%20did%20hair%20for%20would%20come%20back%20the%20next%20day%20just%20to%20see%20me.%20In%20their%20eyes%2C%20I%20was%20like%20their%20fairy%20godmother%20%E2%80%94%20that%20made%20me%20feel%20it%20was%20the%20most%20magical%20job%20that%20I've%20ever%20had.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20that%20job%2C%20I%20also%20helped%20workers%20bring%20food%2C%20merchandise%2C%20and%20toys%20to%20the%20shops.%20I%20didn't%20know%20the%20job%20would%20be%20physically%20demanding%20%E2%80%94%20I%20thought%20I%20would%20just%20be%20doing%20kids'%20hair%2C%20makeup%2C%20and%20nails.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20quit%20after%20just%20four%20months%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20young%2024-year-old%2C%20I%20went%20into%20this%20job%20blindly%20and%20wasn't%20fully%20prepared.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20worked%20from%208%3A30%20a.m.%20until%209%20or%2010%20p.m.%20Before%20starting%20this%20job%2C%20I%20didn't%2C%20or%20couldn't%2C%20conceptualize%20what%20an%2080-hour%20work%20week%20without%20a%20day%20off%20would%20look%C2%A0like%2C%20at%20all.%20There%20was%20no%20work-and-life%20balance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20so%20little%20time%20to%20myself.%20In%20my%20downtime%2C%20I%20didn't%20even%20want%20to%20watch%20TV%20or%20movies.%20Once%20I%20got%2030%20minutes%20into%20watching%2C%20I'd%20rather%20just%20sleep%20because%20I%20was%20so%20tired%20%E2%80%94%20sleeping%20had%20become%20my%20priority.%20The%20only%20%26quot%3Bme%20time%26quot%3B%20I%20would%20have%20for%20myself%20was%20a%20quick%20sheet%20mask%20in%20my%20room%20and%20that's%20all.%20My%20room%20was%20so%20small%20that%20I%20could%20nearly%20touch%20both%20walls%20with%20outstretched%20arms.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20got%20a%20stress%20fracture%20in%20one%20of%20my%20feet%20from%20standing%2080%20hours%20a%20week%20in%20my%20costume%20shoes%20%E2%80%94%20it%20got%20so%20hard%20for%20me%20to%20stand.%20With%20a%20normal%20job%2C%20you%20can%20call%20in%20sick%20if%20you're%20not%20feeling%20well.%20But%20for%20me%2C%20if%20I%20didn't%20show%20up%20to%20work%2C%20my%20manager%20could%20come%20downstairs%20from%20the%20shop%20to%20see%20me%20what%20was%20wrong%2C%20how%20long%20I%20would%20need%20off%2C%20and%20if%20I%20needed%20medical%20attention%2C%20or%20if%20I%20was%20faking%20it.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorking%20on%20the%20cruise%20ship%20meant%20my%20living%20space%20was%20also%20my%20workspace.%20Managers%20and%20coworkers%20could%20spot%20us%20whenever%20we%20were%20out%20at%20night.%20I%20had%20to%20be%20%26quot%3Bon%26quot%3B%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20time%2C%20and%20it%20played%20a%20big%20role%20in%20how%20quickly%20I%20burned%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20fourth%20month%20of%20my%20contract%2C%20I%20felt%20defeated%C2%A0and%20exhausted%20to%20the%20point%20where%20I%20decided%20to%20quit.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22484%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Disney%20Dream%20cruise%20ship%20at%20sea%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651ac690ec74fc00190706b8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22363%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Disney%20Dream%20cruise%20ship%20at%20sea.%3Cp%3EDavid%20Roark%2Fphotographer%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20was%20making%20less%20than%20the%20minimum%20wage%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20worked%20a%20minimum%20of%2070%20hours%20weekly%20and%20got%20paid%20%24423%20a%20week%2C%20so%20it%20was%20about%20%246%20an%20hour.%20There%20was%20no%20overtime%20rate%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20do%20receive%20benefits%2C%20including%20shipboard%20medical%20care%2C%20complimentary%20Disney%20theme%20park%20admission%2C%20discounts%20at%20selected%20resort%20hotels%2C%20and%20Disney%20merchandise%20at%20worldwide%20Disney%20locations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20cruise%20members%20come%20from%20all%20over%20the%20world.%20They're%20making%20US%20dollars%2C%20and%20sometimes%20even%20making%20more%20than%20doctors%20or%20lawyers%20in%20their%20home%20countries.%20One%20girl%20from%20Portugal%20had%20worked%20on%20the%20ships%20for%2010%20years.%20She%20loved%20it%20because%20she%20was%20making%20a%20great%20living%20for%20herself%20and%20for%20her%20family%20overseas%C2%A0%20%E2%80%94%20she%20regularly%20sent%20them%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20cruise%20life%20was%20totally%20worth%20it%20to%20her%2C%20but%20for%20me%2C%20there%20were%20other%20higher-paying%20jobs%20I%20could%20have%20easily%20applied%20to.%20Some%20crew%20members%20on%20the%20ship%20thought%20I%20was%20taking%20a%20job%20from%20someone%20for%20whom%20it%20could%20have%20been%20more%20beneficial%2C%20like%20someone%20who%20needed%20to%20support%20their%20family%20in%20another%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe%20don't%20eat%20the%20same%20food%20as%20the%20guests%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20crew%20members%20eat%20in%20the%20crew%20mess%2C%20a%20large%20cafeteria%20where%20breakfast%2C%20lunch%2C%20and%20dinner%20is%20served.%20There%20is%20a%20small%20salad%20bar%20and%20some%20cooked%20options.%20For%20breakfast%2C%20I%20usually%20ate%20hard-boiled%20eggs.%20For%20lunch%20and%20dinner%2C%20I%20ate%20veggie%20burger%20patties%20(I%20was%20a%20vegetarian%20at%20the%20time).%20During%20holidays%20like%20Thanksgiving%20and%20Christmas%2C%20we%20had%20specialty%20food%20items%20like%20cake%20and%20ice%20cream.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESometimes%20the%20company%20threw%20parties%20for%20us.%20For%20example%2C%20if%20our%20service%20got%20high%20marks%20on%20guest%20surveys%20and%20feedback%2C%20that's%20when%20we%20got%20to%20have%20the%20better-tasting%20guest%20food.%20I%20remember%20they%20brought%20jalapeno%20poppers%20one%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22669%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Buena%20Vista%20Theatre%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651ac6ddec74fc00190706c1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22502%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Buena%20Vista%20Theatre%20inside%20the%20Disney%20Dream%20cruise%20ship.%3Cp%3EMatt%20Stroshane%2Fphotographer%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ENot%20everyone%20on%20the%20ship%20has%20the%20same%20freedoms%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ENot%20everyone%20has%20the%20same%20freedoms%20in%20what%20they%20can%20do%20or%20where%20they%20can%20go%20on%20the%20boat.%20Everything%20above%20the%20deck%20we%20lived%20on%20was%20a%20%26quot%3Bprivilege%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20we%20weren't%20allowed%20to%20roam%20the%20ship%20freely.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20we%20wanted%20to%20go%20to%20spots%20like%20the%20movie%20theater%2C%20we%20had%20to%20call%20our%20manager%20beforehand%20and%20get%20it%20approved%20in%20writing.%20If%20the%20cruise%20was%20very%20full%2C%20we%20might%20need%20to%20free%20up%20room%20for%20guests.%20I%20worked%20in%20the%20shops%2C%20and%20our%20team%20was%20a%20small%20group%20of%2030%20crew%20members.%20We%20were%20able%20to%20go%20to%20more%20places%20on%20the%20ship%20easily.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETypically%2C%20the%20larger%20teams%20weren't%20able%20to%20get%20clearance.%20The%20dining-room%20team%2C%20for%20example%2C%20is%20a%20300-person%20team.%20If%20their%20manager%20gave%20everyone%20on%20that%20team%20permission%20to%20roam%20the%20ship%2C%20guest%20areas%20would%20become%20too%20crowded.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20a%20friend%20who%20was%20a%20server%20in%20the%20dining%20room.%20She%20wasn't%20able%20to%20go%20to%20the%20movie%20theater%20or%20the%20pools%20like%20I%20could.%20She%20was%20only%20allowed%20on%20the%20floor%20that%20she%20lived%20on%20and%20a%20spot%20called%20%26quot%3BDeck%2014%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20is%20a%20small%20outdoor%20smoking%20deck.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20left%20the%20boat%20and%20was%20almost%20put%20on%20Disney's%20'no%20rehire'%20list%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWorking%20on%20the%20ship%20for%20a%20few%20months%20took%20a%20mental%20toll%20on%20me.%20One%20week%20after%20giving%20my%2030-day%20notice%2C%20I%20told%20my%20manager%20that%20I'd%20get%20off%20the%20boat%20the%20next%20time%20we%20ported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20remember%20being%20told%20that%20leaving%20before%20the%2030%20days%20might%20mean%20I%20wouldn't%20be%20able%20to%20work%20for%20Disney%20or%20any%20of%20its%20affiliate%20companies%20like%20ESPN%20and%20ABC.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20was%20a%20scary%20thought%20because%20Disney%20was%20the%20only%20company%20I've%20ever%20worked%20for%20as%20an%20adult.%20But%20my%20foot%20pain%20and%20burnout%20were%20so%20severe%20that%20all%20I%20cared%20about%20at%20that%20point%20was%20getting%20off%20the%20ship.%20So%20I%20left%20after%20four%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWorking%20on%20the%20cruise%20ship%20wasn't%20all%20bad%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWorking%20at%20the%20boutique%20was%20so%20much%20fun.%20I%20also%20had%20a%20wonderful%20roommate%20and%20made%20great%20friends%20with%20the%20people%20living%20in%20my%20hallway.%20It%20felt%20like%20living%20in%20a%20college%20dorm%2C%20and%20we%20all%20became%20close%20friends%20in%20a%20very%20short%20amount%20of%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20unique%20cruise%20line%20experience%20was%20a%20bonding%20opportunity%20that%20brought%20us%20all%20closer.%20Those%20who%20haven't%20lived%20on%20a%20cruise%20line%20just%20wouldn't%20understand.%20In%20all%2C%20I%20cherish%20the%20friendships%20I%20formed%20with%20my%20coworkers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDisney%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EIf%20you've%20worked%20on%20a%20cruise%20line%20and%20want%20to%20share%20your%20story%2C%20email%20Aria%20Yang%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Aayang%40insider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Eayang%40insider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquit-disney-cruise-line-because-of-burnout-long-working-hours-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696325281000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651ac95bec74fc00190706ff%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquit-disney-cruise-line-because-of-burnout-long-working-hours-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Gianna%20Alexis%20quit%20working%20on%20the%20Disney%20Dream%20Cruise%20line%20because%20of%20burnout.%20She%20says%20it%20wasn't%20worth%20the%20stress%20or%20pain%20%E2%80%94%20and%20she%20was%20making%20less%20than%20minimum%20wage.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ayang%40insider.com%20(Aria%20Yang)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A35%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fquit-disney-cruise-line-because-of-burnout-long-working-hours-2023-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Hunter%20Biden%20due%20in%20Delaware%20court%20to%20face%20federal%20gun%20charges%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696325279000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2FF9EC%2Fproduction%2F_131308936_0429798330f581c36384ed799cd9ee51e3a2c8cc0_0_2305_16171000x702.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-us-canada-66949608%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20president's%20son%20faces%20up%20to%2025%20years%20in%20prison%20if%20convicted%20of%20three%20federal%20criminal%20charges.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A36%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-us-canada-66949608%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-