County%2C%20in%20Napa%2C%20and%20in%20Los%20Angeles%20%E2%80%94%20who%20met%20income%20thresholds%20and%20received%20the%20grant.%20While%20all%20three%20described%20parts%20of%20the%20application%20process%20as%20arduous%20%E2%80%94%20the%20end%20result%20has%20been%20positive.%20All%20of%20these%20homeowners%20have%20finished%20their%20ADU%20in%20the%20last%20three%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20said%20they%20would%20recommend%20the%20program%20to%20other%20California%20homeowners.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGetting%20the%20grant%20was%20challenging%2C%20but%20worth%20it.%20I%20would%20recommend%20applying%20for%20similar%20grants%20when%20they%20are%20available%2C%26quot%3B%20Dan%20Romo%2C%20one%20of%20the%20grant%20recipients%2C%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECalifornia%20is%20reviving%20the%20ADU%20grant%20program%20again%2C%20but%20details%20are%20being%20worked%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20their%20stories%2C%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EDaniel%20Romo%2C%2061%20and%20Kristin%20Romo%2C%2063%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224032%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22an%20adu%20made%20from%20a%20garage%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64ecbde2ecb92e0019253f69%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223024%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Romos'%20ADU%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Dan%20and%20Kristin%20Romo%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHome%20location%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Whittier%2C%20California%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECost%20of%20unit%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%24240%2C000%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20the%20unit%20is%20used%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffinance-adu-with-tens-of-thousands-from-california-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThey%20rent%20it%20out%20to%20their%20daughter%20and%20son-in-law%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20live%20there%20with%20their%20two%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20owners'%20story%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDan%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20We%20paid%20%24244%2C000%20when%20we%20bought%20our%20house%2020%20years%20ago%20and%20I%20refinanced%20the%20mortgage%20to%20start%20my%20business%2C%20so%20it's%20even%20larger%20than%20when%20we%20bought%20the%20house.%20Last%20time%20I%20looked%2C%20our%20house%20was%20valued%20at%20%24850%2C000.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKristin%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EIt%20became%20clear%20that%20%E2%80%94%20at%20the%20rate%20we%20were%20going%20on%20our%20mortgage%20and%20with%20the%20rising%20cost%20of%20living%20in%20California%20%E2%80%94%20we%20were%20going%20to%20be%20working%20'til%20we're%2075.%20We%20did%20not%20want%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDan%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Last%20year%2C%20our%20oldest%20daughter%20and%20her%20husband%20realized%20that%2C%20with%20the%20cost%20of%20living%2C%20they%20wouldn't%20be%20able%20to%20afford%20to%20live%20in%20California%20if%20they%20wanted%20to%20own%20a%20home%20to%20raise%20a%20family.%20This%20March%20they%20wound%20up%20moving%20to%20New%20Hampshire.%20Our%20second%20daughter%20had%20just%20had%20her%20first%20child.%20She%20didn't%20want%20to%20move%20out%20of%20the%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKristin%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20After%20receiving%20a%20%2440%2C000%20grant%20from%20the%20state%20and%20taking%20out%20a%20%24200%2C000%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fis-heloc-a-good-idea-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EHELOC%20loan%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20we%20converted%20our%20garage%20into%20a%20modern%20apartment%20that%20our%20daughter%2C%20son-in-law%2C%20and%20grandchildren%20just%20moved%20into.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDan%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Last%20June%2C%20I%20went%20to%20the%20website%20of%20CalHFA%20%E2%80%94%20the%20entity%20that%20was%20distributing%20the%20funds%20%E2%80%94%20only%20to%20hit%20a%20roadblock.%20At%20that%20time%2C%20the%20only%20way%20you%20could%20get%20the%20grant%20was%20you%20had%20to%20go%20through%20a%20state-approved%20vendor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20only%20one%20bank%20that%20would%20allow%20you%20to%20take%20a%20second%20mortgage%2C%20which%20was%20what%20I%20wanted%20because%20my%20interest%20rate%20had%20gone%20down%20to%202.8%25%2C%20and%20they%20were%20pretty%20unresponsive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20didn't%20seem%20possible%2C%20so%20I%20felt%20like%2C%20%26quot%3BOh%2C%20I%20guess%20I%20tried.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20state%20realized%20there%20was%20something%20wrong%20with%20the%20way%20the%20program%20worked%20and%20decided%20to%20work%20with%20nonprofit%20agencies%20to%20help%20them%20distribute%20the%20grants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20applied%20for%20the%20grant%20through%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hppcares.org%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EHPP%20Cares%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%2C%20at%20first%2C%20my%20application%20fell%20through%20the%20cracks.%20But%20then%2C%20finally%2C%20I%20was%20able%20to%20get%20the%20grant.%20I%20received%20the%20money%20by%20late%20October%20or%20early%20November.%20It%20was%20a%20challenging%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20applied%20for%20the%20grant%2C%20I%20had%20to%20qualify.%20We%20had%20to%20have%20a%20certain%20amount%20of%20income%2C%20then%20we%20had%20to%20demonstrate%20that%20this%20was%20our%20home%20and%20primary%20residence.%20Once%20I%20submitted%20that%2C%20they%20also%20requested%20tax%20returns.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20was%20approved%20for%20the%20grant%2C%20they%20required%20that%20I%20submit%20the%20contractor's%20budget%20and%20the%20cost%20of%20the%20construction.%20Then%2C%20they%20deducted%20the%20grant%20amount%20from%20that%20budget.%20I%20had%20to%20put%20the%20remaining%20amount%20in%20an%20escrow%20account%2C%20which%20was%20something%20that%20this%20state%20required.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKristin%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20When%20I%20heard%20all%20that%2C%20it%20gave%20me%20peace%20of%20mind.%20I%20felt%20like%20this%20the%20way%20that%20the%20state%20was%20taking%20care%20of%20their%20money.%20They%20were%20really%20making%20sure%20that%20people%20weren't%20trying%20to%20do%20something%20underhanded.%20So%2C%20in%20some%20ways%2C%20I%20felt%20protected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDan%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20After%20the%20cost%20of%20administrative%20fees%2C%20we%20actually%20only%20got%20around%20%2433%2C000.%20I%20was%20grateful%20for%20that%2C%20of%20course%2C%20but%20the%20sum%20of%20the%20grant%20was%20a%20little%20misleading.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGetting%20the%20grant%20was%20challenging%2C%20but%20worth%20it.%20I%20would%20recommend%20applying%20for%20similar%20grants%20when%20they%20are%20available.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20encourage%20people%20to%20humble%20themselves%20and%20have%20a%20growth%20mindset%20and%20open%20to%20the%20possibility%20of%20something%20that%20is%20completely%20foreign.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EJakota%20Rivas%2C%2046%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22a%20blue%20ADU%20sits%20on%20a%20construction%20site%20with%20trees%20around%20it.%20Jakota%20Rivas%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651ad6c94ff1e30019476971%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJakota%20Rivas'%20ADU%3Cp%3EEric%20Santucci%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHome%20location%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Napa%2C%20California%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECost%20of%20unit%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%24124%2C000%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20the%20unit%20is%20used%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Rivas%20rents%20the%20unit%20out%20to%20her%20two%20eldest%20children%2C%20who%20are%2018%20and%2019%20years%20old.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20owner's%20story%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EWe%20have%20four%20kids%20and%20we%20moved%20from%20southern%20California%20to%20northern%20California%20right%20when%20the%20pandemic%20shutdowns%20started%2C%20in%20March%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20lived%20out%20of%20a%20hotel%20for%20a%20period%20of%20time%20when%20everything%20was%20shut%20down%2C%20and%20then%20we%20rented%20for%20some%20time.%20We%20looked%20at%20over%2040%20houses%20to%20buy%2C%20we%20put%20in%20nine%20offers%20before%20we%20finally%20got%20to%20the%20house%20we%20bought%2C%20in%20December%202020%20%E2%80%94%20nearly%20a%20year%20after%20we%20started%20our%20search.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20we%20bought%20the%20house%2C%20I%20had%20talked%20about%20building%20an%20ADU%2C%20but%20my%20husband%20wasn't%20sold.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20house%20has%20got%20three%20bedrooms%2C%20and%20then%20it's%20got%20a%20sunroom%20off%20the%20kitchen.%20The%20sunroom%20was%20huge.%20This%20was%20your%20typical%201980s%20sunroom%20with%20skylights%2C%20single%20pane%20windows.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20had%20to%20do%20a%20lot%20of%20renovations%20on%20it%20to%20make%20it%20into%20a%20room%20for%20our%20sons.%20One%20of%20the%20issues%20was%20there%20was%20mold%20in%20the%20handling%20out%20there%20so%20we%20had%20to%20replace%20all%20that%3B%20we%20put%20screens%20on%20all%20the%20windows%20so%20the%20boys%20could%20open%20that%20up.%20We%20put%20heaters%20on%20the%20floor%20so%20that%20they%20would%20be%20warmer%20because%20it's%20not%20insulated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20of%20the%20kids%20stayed%20in%20the%20sunroom.%20We%20had%20made%20all%20of%20these%20changes%20but%20despite%20that%20this%20was%20our%20first%20winter%20in%20Northern%20California%20%E2%80%94%20so%20we%20underestimated%20just%20how%20cold%20it%20would%20get.%20The%20two%20kids%20in%20the%20room%20were%20freezing%2C%20so%20we%20knew%20we%20needed%20to%20do%20something.%20Luckily%2C%20around%20that%20time%2C%20I%20had%20gotten%20a%20promotion%2C%20so%20we%20had%20some%20extra%20money%20to%20do%20something.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20our%20two%20oldest%20kids%20were%20both%20about%20to%20graduate%20high%20school.%20My%20daughter%20graduated%20two%20years%20early%20from%20high%20school%20and%20my%20son%20was%20a%20senior.%20I%20said%20why%20don't%20we%20build%20them%20an%20ADU%20and%20then%20they%20can%20pay%20rent%20to%20live%20there%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20refinanced%20in%20April%2C%20and%20we%20tore%20the%20sunroom%20down%20in%20May.%20We%20finally%20got%20our%20permits%20submitted%20for%20that%20October%2C%20and%20that's%20when%20we%20got%20the%20grant%2C%20too.%20Come%20January%2C%20we're%20finally%20breaking%20ground%2C%20and%20all%20of%20a%20sudden%20I%20hear%20about%20this%20forgivable%20loan%20that%20Napa%20County%20is%20giving%20out.%20We%20applied%20and%20we%20got%20that.%20So%20this%20was%20all%20money%20that%20we%20weren't%20budgeting%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20allowed%20us%20to%20then%20go%20ahead%20and%20fix%20all%20the%20grass%20in%20the%20backyard%2C%20it%20allowed%20us%20to%20build%20the%20loft%20in%20our%20ADU%20after%20it%20was%20finished%20with%20for%20our%20daughter.%20It%20allowed%20us%20to%20pay%20off%20my%20car.%20We%20are%20charging%20our%20kids%20for%20rent.%20So%20%241%2C000%20a%20month%2C%20%24500%20each.%20Technically%20based%20on%20the%20income%20guidelines%2C%20I%20think%20we%20can%20charge%20up%20to%20%242%2C100.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20love%20it%20and%20it's%20just%20amazing.%20Altogether%2C%20we%20paid%20%24124%2C000%20out%20of%20pocket%2C%20got%20the%20%2440%2C000%20from%20the%20state%2C%20and%20a%20forgivable%20loan%20of%20%2467%2C500.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ERosario%2C%2066%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223005%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20ADU%20Rosario%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651adbab4ff1e30019476b3f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222346%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERosario's%20ADU%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Rosario%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHome%20location%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Los%20Angeles%2C%20California%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECost%20of%20unit%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%24300%2C000%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20the%20unit%20is%20used%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%20Rosario%20lives%20in%20the%20handicapped-accessible%20ADU%2C%20while%20his%20sister%20lives%20in%20the%20main%20house%20on%20the%20property.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ERosario's%20last%20name%20is%20not%20included%20due%20to%20privacy%20concerns.%20His%20last%20name%20is%20known%20to%20Insider%20and%20his%20identity%20has%20been%20verified.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20owner's%20story%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EI%20am%20handicapped%20and%20most%20of%20the%20time%20I%20need%20a%20wheelchair%20and%20a%20walker.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20decided%20to%20build%20an%20ADU%20on%20my%20property%20that's%20handicap%20accessible%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0so%2C%20wider%20doors%20to%20the%20bathroom%2C%20to%20the%20bedroom%2C%20making%20it%20easy%20to%20get%20around%20in%20a%20wheelchair.%20In%20the%20shower%2C%20I%20can%20go%20in%20with%20my%20walker%20because%20it's%20the%20same%20level%20as%20the%20floor.%20I%20also%20have%20a%20ramp%20that%20leads%20to%20the%20front%20door.%20My%20favorite%20room%20is%20the%20kitchen%20%E2%80%94%20I%20designed%20each%20aspect%20of%20it%20myself.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ADU%20is%20611-square-feet%2C%20and%20is%20located%20on%20the%20detached%20garage%20on%20the%20property%20that%20my%20sister%20and%20I%20share.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EShe%20lives%20in%20the%20house.%20With%20furnishings%20and%20all%2C%20it%20cost%20%24300%2C000.%20I%20paid%20for%20the%20majority%20of%20the%20project%20with%20my%20savings%2C%20and%20the%20rest%20with%20the%20%2440%2C000%20California%20ADU%20grant.%20I%20did%20not%20take%20out%20any%20loans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20am%20very%20happy%20with%20my%20ADU%20but%20there%20was%20stuff%20about%20the%20grant%20I%20wish%20I%20had%20known%20before%20I%20started.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20administrative%20fees%20and%20taxes%20on%20the%20grant%20itself%2C%20I%20only%20cleared%20%2421%2C355%20out%20of%20the%20whole%20grant%2C%20which%20I%20used%20to%20reimburse%20myself%20for%20the%20pre-construction%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20a%20kick%20in%20the%20pants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20top%20of%20that%2C%20there%20were%20extra%20costs%20that%20were%20not%20in%20the%20original%20quote.%20The%20most%20difficult%20part%20of%20the%20process%20was%20when%20I%20needed%20to%20hire%20an%20engineer%20for%20an%20extra%20%2420%2C000%2C%20after%20the%20project%20had%20already%20started.%20I%20had%20a%20wall%20adjacent%20to%20my%20neighbor%2C%20and%20to%20keep%20that%20wall%2C%20I%20needed%20to%20get%20an%20engineer%2C%20because%20the%20foundation%20underneath%20wasn't%20good%20enough%20to%20be%20approved%20by%20the%20city.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20I%20would%20recommend%20applying%20to%20the%20grant%20if%20a%20friend%20wanted%20to%20build%20an%20ADU%2C%20but%20I%20would%20definitely%20need%20to%20explain%20the%20situation%3A%20you're%20not%20going%20to%20get%20the%20%2440%2C000%2C%20you're%20only%20going%20to%20get%20half%20if%20you're%20lucky.%20And%20there%20may%20be%20extra%20costs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20ultimately%2C%20I%20love%20my%20new%20home.%20I%20am%20tickled%20to%20death%20about%20how%20it%20came%20out%2C%20and%20was%20happy%20to%20get%20the%20grant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiny-home-adu-california-how-to-use-40000-grant-affordability-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696323661000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F651aef5e4ff1e3001947720b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftiny-home-adu-california-how-to-use-40000-grant-affordability-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20families%20told%20Insider%20it%20helped%20them%20increase%20their%20property%20value%2C%20keep%20their%20adult%20children%20in%20the%20area%2C%20and%20add%20living%20space%20to%20their%20property.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22kneubauer%40insi