iew-jds-bjp-alliance-congress-nitish-kumar-asked-after-bjp-tie-up-deve-gowda-reveals-india-invite-4445018%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Aircraft-Sized%20Asteroid%20Heading%20Towards%20Earth.%20Close%20Approach%20On...%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EAn%20asteroid%20drifts%20aimlessly%20through%20the%20vast%20expanse%20of%20space.%20With%20no%20fixed%20path%20or%20destination%2C%20the%20'cosmic%20nomad'%20sometimes%20comes%20in%20close%20contact%20with%20other%20space%20objects%20and%20planets%20due%20to%20gravitational%20forces.%20Space%20agencies%20like%20NASA%20have%20developed%20programmes%20to%20keep%20a%20watch%20on%20these%20celestial%20wanderers%20so%20that%20our%20planet%20can%20be%20kept%20safe%20from%20any%20catastrophic%20impact.%20The%20American%20space%20agency%20has%20even%20created%20a%20dedicated%20page%20listing%20the%20asteroids%20that%20will%20pass%20very%20close%20to%20the%20Earth.%20And%20that%20list%20shows%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.jpl.nasa.gov%2Fasteroid-watch%2Fnext-five-approaches%5C%22%3EAsteroid%202023%20SN6%3C%2Fa%3E%20racing%20towards%20out%20home%20planet.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20aircraft-sized%20space%20rock%20will%20pass%20cross%20Earth%20at%20a%20distance%20of%204.8%20million%20kilometres%20on%20October%204%20(Wednesday)%20-%20still%20close%20considering%20distance%20in%20the%20space%20is%20measured%20in%20astronomical%20terms.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20NASA%20data%2C%20the%20asteroid%20is%20travelling%20at%20a%20speed%20of%2030%2C564%20kilometres%20per%20hour.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20space%20agency's%20Centre%20for%20Near%20Earth%20Object%20Studies%20(CNEOS)%20hasn't%20classified%20the%20asteroid%20as%20a%20potentially%20hazardous%20object.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20belongs%20to%20the%20Apollo%20group%20of%20Near-Earth%20Asteroids%2C%20named%20after%20the%201862%20Apollo%20asteroid%2C%20discovered%20by%20German%20astronomer%20Karl%20Reinmuth%20in%20the%201930s.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAsteroids%2C%20space%20rocks%20that%20are%20remnants%20from%20the%20formation%20of%20our%20solar%20system%2C%20often%20tumble%20and%20spin%2C%20and%20are%20propelled%20forward%20by%20the%20momentum%20of%20its%20birthplace.%20Their%20surface%2C%20weathered%20by%20eons%20of%20cosmic%20radiation%20and%20micrometeoroid%20impacts%2C%20tell%20the%20story%20of%20asteroids'%20journey%20through%20the%20depths%20of%20the%20universe.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20NASA%20launched%20a%20mission%20to%20deflect%20an%20asteroid%20hurtling%20towards%20the%20Earth%20as%20part%20of%20its%20planetary%20defence%20mechanism.%20It%20is%20called%20Double%20Asteroid%20Redirection%20Test%20or%20DART.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20first%20phase%2C%20a%20spacecraft%20sent%20by%20NASA%20scientists%20crashed%20into%20Dimorphos%2C%20its%20targeted%20asteroid%2C%20on%20September%2026%2C%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20cube-shaped%20%26quot%3Bimpactor%26quot%3B%20vehicle%2C%20roughly%20the%20size%20of%20a%20vending%20machine%2C%20flew%20into%20the%20football%20stadium-sized%20asteroid%20about%2011%20million%20km%20from%20Earth.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696320600000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2022-11%2F92e7e9pg_asteroid-generic_625x300_01_November_22.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Faircraft-sized-asteroid-heading-towards-earth-close-approach-on-4445072%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22According%20to%20NASA%20data%2C%20the%20asteroid%20is%20travelling%20at%20a%20speed%20of%2030%2C564%20kilometres%20per%20hour.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A11%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Faircraft-sized-asteroid-heading-towards-earth-close-approach-on-4445072%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Faircraft-sized-asteroid-heading-towards-earth-close-approach-on-4445072%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fairc