f%20that%20were%20to%20be%20the%20case%2C%20I%20fully%20agree%20with%20you%20that%20we%20cannot%20go%20down%20and%20say%20that%20%E2%80%98Okay%20we%20want%20a%20local%20government%E2%80%99%2C%20because%20a%20local%20government%20would%20possibly%20have%20been%20riddled%20with%20the%20problems%20that%20you%20mentioned.%20But%20now%20we%20can%20see%20that%20in%201990%2C%20when%20the%2073rd%20and%2074th%20Amendment%20were%20enacted%20by%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20government%2C%20what%20are%20we%20talking%20about%3F%20We%20are%20talking%20about%20decentralisation.%20What%20is%20decentralisation%3F%20Decentralisation%20is%20greater%20power%20to%20the%20people%2C%20bringing%20the%20power%20of%20sovereign%20power%20closer%20to%20the%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20But%20surely%20you%20are%20not%20saying%20that%20the%20absence%20of%20the%20panchayat%20laws%20in%201947%2C%201948%2C%201949%20meant%20that%20the%20whole%20constitution%20therefore%20became%20colonial%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20No%2C%20not%20at%20all.%20That%20is%20a%20very%20simplistic%20claim%20to%20make.%20But%20there%20was%20an%20alternative%20idea%20that%20was%20proposed.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20But%20was%20there%3F%20That%E2%80%99s%20the%20point%20I%E2%80%99m%20making.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20Yes.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20The%20alternative%20idea%20years%20would%20have%20inevitably%20led%20to%20a%20situation%20where%20individuals%20would%20have%20been%20submerged%20under%20communities%2C%20where%20the%20traditions%20of%20caste%2C%20khap%20and%20community%20would%20have%20gotten%20priority%20over%20the%20right%20of%20a%20single%20man%20or%20single%20woman.%20That%20would%20have%20been%20un-modern.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EThat%E2%80%99s%20right.%20The%20fact%20that%20we%20are%20still%20asking%20that%20question%2C%20and%20it%20is%20a%20very%20legitimate%20question%20to%20ask%20even%2075%20years%20later%2C%20shows%20that%20there%20is%20much%20work%20to%20be%20done%20in%20trying%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20individual%20and%20community%20can%20live%20in%20harmonious%20coexistence%20with%20power%20vested%20at%20a%20local%20level.%20It%20is%20not%20an%20inevitability.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EBut%20that%20argument%20you%E2%80%99re%20making%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20mean%20that%20the%20constitution%20is%20colonial%2C%20it%20simply%20means%20that%20some%20of%20the%20rights%20the%20constitution%20confers%20on%20people%20haven%E2%80%99t%20actually%20been%20implemented%20and%20haven%E2%80%99t%20gone%20down%20far%20enough.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20it%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20been%20perfectly%20executed.%20Imperfection%20in%20the%20execution%20means%20you%20still%20have%20these%20problems%20at%20ground%20level.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20No%2C%20but%20the%20constitution%20didn%E2%80%99t%20envisage%20any%20significant%20power%20at%20the%20ground%20level.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20fact%20that%20the%20constitution%20envisages%20a%20very%20powerful%20union%20government%20in%20general.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20I%20come%20to%20the%20power%20of%20the%20union%20government%20in%20a%20moment%E2%80%99s%20time%2C%20but%20let%E2%80%99s%20take%20up%20this%20point%20you%E2%80%99re%20making%2C%20that%20because%20the%20constitution%20didn%E2%80%99t%20envisage%20significant%20part%20at%20the%20local%20village%20level%20or%20ground%20level%2C%20therefore%20it%E2%80%99s%20colonial.%20That%20is%20what%20I%E2%80%99m%20disputing.%20It%20may%20not%20have%20transferred%20power%20decentralised%20all%20the%20way%20to%20the%20bottom%2C%20but%20the%20conclusion%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20mean%20that%20therefore%20it%E2%80%99s%20colonial.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20You%E2%80%99re%20right%2C%20in%20the%20sense%