0the%20right%20to%20vote%20to%20every%20Indian%20over%20the%20age%20of%2018%2C%20regardless%20of%20caste%2C%20creed%20or%20gender%2C%20something%20that%20didn%E2%80%99t%20happen%20in%20the%20UK%20till%201918.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20That%E2%80%99s%20right.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EIt%20didn%E2%80%99t%20happen%20in%20America%20till%201920%2C%20and%20if%20you%20look%20at%20the%20situation%20facing%20Blacks%20not%20till%20the%20mid%2060s.%20Yet%20you%20still%20call%20it%20a%20colonial%20constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20All%20of%20what%20you%20said%2C%20I%20fully%20agree%20with.%20This%20is%20the%20standard%20script%20of%20the%20constitution%20of%20India%20that%20we%20all%20have%20been%20brought%20up%20with%20for%2075%20years%2C%20and%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20reason%20why%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20standard%20script%2C%20because%20it%E2%80%99s%20true.%20All%20these%20things%20that%20you%20mention%20are%20true.%20The%20fact%20is%20that%2C%20as%20I%20write%20in%20my%20book%2C%20there%20is%20a%20lot%20to%20celebrate%20in%20this%20constitution.%20Merely%20the%20fact%20that%20we%20call%20it%20a%20%E2%80%98colonial%20constitution%E2%80%99%20does%20not%20mean%20that%20it%20should%20be%20rubbished%2C%20or%20thrown%20into%20the%20dustbin%2C%20not%20at%20all.%20That%20is%20not%20my%20claim.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20It%E2%80%99s%20only%20colonial%20in%20that%20it%20uses%20and%20adopts%20the%20outline%20formal%20structure%20of%20the%20Government%20of%20India%20Act%2C%20having%20kept%20that%20structure%20of%20administration%20and%20governance%20intact.%20It%E2%80%99s%20actually%20infused%20into%20the%20constitution%20a%20million%20things%20that%20the%20British%20didn%E2%80%99t%20have.%20The%20structure%20may%20be%20that%20of%20the%20act%2C%20yes%2C%20but%20what%20lies%20behind%20the%20structure%20in%20terms%20of%20rights%20is%20so%20different.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EYes%2C%20so%20what%20lies%20behind%20the%20structure%20as%20you%20said%20is%20rights%2C%20but%20let%E2%80%99s%20see%20the%20other%20side%20of%20the%20coin.%20What%20also%20lies%20is%20a%20huge%20slew%20of%20restrictions%20on%20those%20rights%2C%20and%20I%20think%20this%20is%20very%20important%20for%20us%20to%20understand%3A%20why%20is%20it%20that%20every%20government%20in%20democratic%20India%2C%20irrespective%20of%20political%20party%2C%20has%20not%20removed%20the%20law%20on%20sedition%3F%20Why%20is%20that%20the%20case%3F%20The%20case%20is%20because%20constitutionally%2C%20what%20we%20have%20set%20up%20is%20a%20law%20and%20order%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20Forgive%20me%2C%20you%E2%80%99re%20an%20expert%20and%20I%20am%20not.%20But%20if%20I%20am%20correct%2C%20the%20first%20couple%20of%20high%20court%20judgments%20actually%20struck%20down%20sedition%20that%E2%80%99s%20right%20and%20that%E2%80%99s%20why%20the%20first%20amendment%20was%20passed%20to%20bring%20sedition%20back%20in.%20So%20the%20original%20constitution%20as%20interpreted%20originally%2C%20actually%20didn%E2%80%99t%20have%20sedition%20%E2%80%93%20it%20was%20the%20first%20amendment%20that%20brought%20it%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20Well%2C%20this%20is%20a%20complicated%20story%20because%20it%20was%20always%20intended%20to%20have%20it.%20But%20the%20judges%20held%20otherwise%2C%20and%20so%20Nehru%20brought%20it%20back%2C%20because%20he%20felt%20that%20we%20need%20it%20because%20of%20Gopala%20and%20so%20on.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EThe%20reason%20that%20judges%20thought%20otherwise%20is%20because%20the%20constitution%20gave%20them%20grounds%20to%20do%20so.%20The%20attack%20you%E2%80%99re%20making%20on%20the%20constitution%2C%20that%20it%20retains%20sedition%2C%20is%20actually%20invalidated%20by%20the%20fact%20that%20courts%20like%20I%20think%20it%20was%20the%20Punjab%20high%20court%20that%20actually%20struck%20it%20down%2C%20believing%20that%20the%20constitution%20did%20not%20permit%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3ESo%20that%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20the%20solution.%20It%20was%20your%20namesake%20actually%2C%20Romesh%20Thapar%20%E2%80%93%20a%20very%20famous%20case%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20which%20actually%20said%20that%20the%20freedom%20of%20speech%20and%20restriction%20cannot%20not%20be%20limited%20by%2C%20and%20in%20that%20case%20it%20was%20the%20magazine%20which%20was%20called%20%3Cem%3ECross%20Roads%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0and%20%3Cem%3EOrganiser%3C%2Fem%3E%20was%20also%20the%20RSS%20magazine%20which%20was%20also%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20Perhaps%20out%20of%20honesty%20I%20should%20admit%20he%E2%80%99s%20my%20first%20cousin.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20All%20right%2C%20should%20have%20known%20that%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20connection.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EBut%20let%E2%80%99s%20come%20back%20to%20this%3A%20the%20important%20thing%20and%20this%20is%20again%20apparent%20in%20your%20book%2C%20is%20that%20on%20the%20one%20hand%20you%20call%20the%20constitutional%20colonial%20and%20I%E2%80%99m%20disputing%20that%20because%20of%20the%20enormous%20number%20of%20rights%20it%20confers%2C%20which%20no%20colony%20ever%20had%2C%20no%20empire%20would%20ever%20have%20given.%20But%20you%20have%20another%2C%20I%20think%20odd%20point%20in%20that.%20You%20say%20that%20on%20the%20one%20hand%20is%20colonial%2C%20and%20on%20the%20other%20you%20go%20to%20a%20great%20extent%20to%20point%20out%20how%20the%20constitutional%20advisor%20B.%20N.%20Rao%20had%20made%20an%20enormous%20effort%20to%20adapt%20aspects%20of%20western%20constitutions%20which%20we%20were%20taking%20on%2C%20because%20he%20wanted%20to%20ensure%20that%20those%20aspects%20fitted%20India%E2%80%99s%20reality.%20This%20is%20what%20you%20write%2C%20%E2%80%9CDuring%20his%20extensive%20travels%20abroad%2C%20Rao%20realised%20that%20a%20postcolonial%20constitution%20like%20India%E2%80%99s%20could%20not%20simply%20replicate%20a%20western%20stereotype.%20It%20would%20have%20to%20adapt%20such%20models%20to%20suit%20the%20needs%20of%20an%20aspiring%20constitutional%20democracy%E2%80%9D.%20Very%20importantly%20you%20add%2C%20%E2%80%9CBold%2C%20original%20thinking%20was%20the%20need%20of%20the%20hour%20to%20decolonise%20the%20constitution%E2%80%9D.%20If%20what%20you%20say%20about%20Rao%20is%20right%2C%20then%20clearly%20it%20can%E2%80%99t%20be%20that%20the%20constitution%20that%20emerged%20is%20colonial.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20263px)%2085vw%2C%20263px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F01%2F04135035%2FBN_Rau_1988_stamp_of_India.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22263%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F01%2F04135035%2FBN_Rau_1988_stamp_of_India.jpg%20666w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F01%2F04135035%2FBN_Rau_1988_stamp_of_India-205x300.jpg%20205w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-424982%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22385%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20postal%20stamp%20of%20B.N.%20Rau.%20Photo%3A%20Wikimedia%20Commons%2F%20India%20Post%2C%20Government%20of%20India%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20That%E2%80%99s%20right.%20I%E2%80%99m%20never%20doubting%20the%20intention%20of%20any%20of%20the%20framers%2C%20including%20Rao.%20I%20think%20the%20idea%20always%20was%20that%20we%20need%20a%20system%20that%20works%20for%20India.%20The%20question%20is%20what%20would%20work%20for%20India%3F%20Here%2C%20the%20idea%20that%20came%20to%20the%20framers%20as%20almost%20natural%20is%20that%20we%20need%20a%20large%20state%20that%20is%20based%20on%20the%20centre%E2%80%99s%20power%20in%20New%20Delhi%2C%20and%20that%20is%20what%20will%20work%20wonders%20for%20India.%20At%20its%20core%2C%20this%20idea%20that%20a%20country%20as%20large%20as%20India%20will%20be%20ruled%20with%20a%20from%20a%20powerful%20centre%20in%20New%20Delhi%2C%20with%20powers%20to%20ensure%20law%20and%20order%2C%20preventive%20detention%20and%20all%20kinds%20of%20activities%20that%20restrict%20rights%20of%20individuals%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3ELaw%20and%20order%20actually%20was%20passed%20down%20to%20state%20levels.%20Preventive%20detention%20may%20not%20have%20been%2C%20law%20and%20order%20actually%20is%20a%20state%20prerogative.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20I%20use%20law%20and%20order%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20normative%20conception%20of%20law%20and%20order%2C%20and%20not%20the%20legal%20question%20of%20who%20has%20competence%20to%20deal%20with%20the%20question.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20You%E2%80%99re%20now%20coming%20to%20the%20second%20broad%20argument%20on%20which%20you%20base%20your%20claim%20that%20India%E2%80%99s%20constitution%20is%20colonial%2C%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20constitution%20created%20a%20strong%20central%20government%20in%20Delhi.%20This%20is%20what%20you%20write%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Indian%20constitution%20is%20colonial%20in%20a%20more%20conceptual%20sense.%20It%20sets%20up%20a%20government%20that%20towers%20over%20the%20citizen%2C%20much%20like%20colonial%20governments%20tend%20to%20do%E2%80%9D.%20But%20I%20put%20it%20to%20you%2C%20one%2C%20that%20was%20a%20reasonable%20response%20to%20the%20trauma%20of%20Partition%2C%20and%20as%20you%20were%20hinting%20a%20moment%20ago%20it%20was%20probably%20a%20very%20necessary%20response%20to%20the%20fact%20that%20India%20is%20a%20heterogeneous%20country%2C%20with%20a%20multiplicity%20of%20ethnicities%2C%20castes%2C%20creeds%2C%20cultures%2C%20cuisines%20and%20languages.%20You%20needed%20a%20strong%20centre%20to%20hold%20this%20country%20together.%20Therefore%20this%20strong%20centre%20is%20not%20a%20colonial%20influence%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20reflection%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20reality.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EThat%E2%80%99s%20right.%20So%20as%20I%20say%20in%20the%20book%2C%20the%20book%20is%20an%20origin%20story%20%E2%80%93%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20story%20of%20how%20we%20got%20the%20constitution.%20I%20certainly%20have%20some%20views%20in%20terms%20of%20what%20it%20should%20be%2C%20but%20that%E2%80%99s%20not%20what%20the%20book%20is%20about.%20It%E2%80%99s%20neither%20a%20celebration%20nor%20a%20critique%20of%20the%20constitution%2C%20but%20a%20fact%20of%20what%20the%20framers%20were%20thinking%20and%20to%20set%20the%20context%20straight%20on%20that.%20As%20far%20as%20the%20specific%20points%20that%20you%20make%2C%20of%20whether%20it%20is%20a%20reasonable%20choice%2C%20yes%20of%20course%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20reasonable%20choice%20to%20make.%20We%20were%2C%20as%20as%20I%20said%2C%20on%20the%209th%20of%20December%201946%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EExcuse%20me%2C%20I%E2%80%99m%20interrupting%2C%20but%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20the%20reasonableness%20of%20the%20choice%20I%E2%80%99m%20questioning%2C%20nor%20you.%20What%20I%E2%80%99m%20questioning%20is%20that%20you%20call%20a%20strong%20central%20government%20colonial.%20I%E2%80%99m%20saying%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20colonial%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20reflection%20of%20understanding%20the%20reality%20that%20without%20a%20strong%20central%20government%2C%20this%20country%20would%20have%20fallen%20apart.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EEverything%20has%20many%20impulses.%20I%20think%20as%20you%20rightly%20say%2C%20that%20one%20of%20the%20key%20things%20that%20the%20framers%20are%20bothered%20about%20in%201947%20%E2%80%93%20there%E2%80%99s%20Partition%20that%E2%80%99s%20happening%20is%20that%20there%20must%20not%20be%20secession%20of%20this%20kind%2C%20and%20we%20must%20ensure%20that%20there%20must%20be%20a%20strong%20centre%20to%20make%20that%20happen.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20Also%2C%20they%20were%20bringing%20together%20a%20patchwork%20of%20560%20odd%20princely%20states%20that%20were%20not%20directly%20under%20British%20control%2C%20although%20they%20were%20closely%20allied%20to%20it.%20Once%20again%2C%20there%20was%20a%20great%20fear%20that%20if%20you%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20a%20strong%20centre%2C%20these%20562%20states%20that%20have%20never%20been%20united%20or%20part%20of%20India%20in%20the%20government%20sense%2C%20would%20actually%20fracture%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EThat%E2%80%99s%20right%2C%20and%20I%20think%20we%20need%20to%20just%20unpack%20what%20we%20mean%20by%20a%20strong%20centre.%20I%20think%20that%E2%80%99s%20where%20much%20of%20the%20discussion%20is%20in%20the%20book%2C%20is%20the%20fact%20that%20at%20that%20point%20of%20time%20as%20you%20remember%20the%20Cabinet%20Mission%20plan%20had%20come%20in.%20The%20Cabinet%20Mission%20plan%20had%20said%20that%20the%20central%20government%20would%20have%20only%20three%20subjects%20%E2%80%93%20Foreign%20Affairs%2C%20Defense%20and%20Communications%20%E2%80%93%20broadly%20I%20am%20simplifying%20here.%20Everything%20else%20would%20go%20to%20the%20states.%20This%20was%20the%20last%20ditch%20effort.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EStates%20grouped%20in%20three.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EYes%2C%3Cb%3E%20%3C%2Fb%3Estates%20grouped%20in%20three.%20This%20was%20a%20last%20ditch%20effort%20to%20try%20and%20keep%20Pakistan%20as%20part%20of%20the%20country.%20But%20when%20it%20was%20realised%20that%20this%20was%20not%20going%20to%20happen%2C%20and%20it%E2%80%99s%20pretty%20incredible%20to%20look%20at%20those%20constituent%20assembly%20debates%2C%20there%20was%20an%20immediate%20reversion%20to%20the%20fact%20that%20India%20must%20be%20a%20strong%20central%20union%20government%20with%20powers%3B%20some%20powers%20devolved%20to%20the%20states%20and%20a%20federation%20with%20residuary%20powers%20that%20will%20continue%20to%20remain%20with%20the%20centre.%20There%20will%20be%20no%20village%20level%20units%20or%20local%20municipal%20units%20at%20all%2C%20as%20Mahatma%20Gandhi%20had%20been%20asking%20for%20for%20the%20last%2020%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EBut%20there%20was%20another%20reason%20why%20people%20also%20decided%20after%20the%20failure%20of%20the%20Cabinet%20Mission%20plan%20that%20they%20needed%20a%20strong%20centre%2C%20that%20Jinnah%20actually%20agreed%20to%20the%20Cabinet%20Mission%20plan.%20The%20reason%20he%20did%20is%20because%20he%20realised%20this%20effectively%2C%20if%20not%20in%20name%2C%20gave%20him%20a%20Pakistan%20both%20in%20the%20East%20and%20the%20West.%20The%20federal%20or%20confederate%20nature%20of%20that%20plan%20would%20have%20given%20him%20the%20autonomy%20he%20wanted.%20That%20was%20another%20reason%20you%20have%20to%20have%20a%20strong%20centre%2C%20and%20that%E2%80%99s%20otherwise%20this%20sort%20of%20confederacy%20will%20break%20up%20our%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20Absolutely.%20Let%20me%20be%20upfront.%20The%20Cabinet%20Mission%20plan%20was%20completely%20unworkable.%20That%20is%20why%20what%20happened%20was%20that%20the%20idea%20of%20a%20weak%20centre%20and%20stronger%20states%20became%20conflated%20with%20an%20unworkable%20idea%20of%20a%20Cabinet%20Mission%20plan.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20But%20are%20you%20not%20noticing%20the%20paradox%20in%20what%20you%E2%80%99re%20saying%3F%20The%20Cabinet%20Mission%20plan%20was%20colonial.%20Had%20we%20accepted%20the%20confederal%20nature%20that%20it%20imposed%20on%20the%20country%2C%20then%20you%20could%20say%20we%20went%20for%20a%20colonial%20architecture.%20What%20we%20opted%20for%20was%20the%20opposite%20of%20the%20Cabinet%20Mission%20plan.%20Therefore%20you%20can%E2%80%99t%20call%20it%20colonial.%20That%20was%20India%E2%80%99s%20own%20decision%20that%20we%20need%20a%20strong%20centre.%20It%E2%80%99s%20the%20colonial%20thing%20that%20would%20have%20been%20the%20Cabinet%20Mission%20plan.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20Well%20certainly%20both%20are%20colonial%2C%20this%20is%20what%20I%20would%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EBut%20look%20at%20this.%20Let%20me%20point%20out%20a%20second%20problem%2C%20and%20I%E2%80%99m%20using%20your%20phrase%20with%20your%20claim%2C%20that%20a%20government%20that%20%E2%80%98towers%20over%20the%20citizens%20is%20colonial%E2%80%99.%20After%20the%20Meiji%20Restoration%20in%20Japan%2C%20you%20had%20a%20government%20that%20towered%20over%20the%20citizens.%20In%20fact%2C%20the%20Emperor%20was%20considered%20God%2C%20yet%20Japan%20has%20had%20no%20colonial%20experience%20in%20its%20history.%20Indeed%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20been%20a%20colonising%20country%20as%20far%20as%20Korea%20and%20parts%20of%20China%20are%20concerned.%20So%20this%20belief%20that%20a%20government%20that%20towers%20over%20its%20citizens%20is%20colonial%2C%20is%20not%20true.%20The%20Japanese%20model%20is%20not%20colonial%2C%20and%20it%20towers%20over%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EThere%20are%20many%20models%20which%20as%20you%20rightly%20point%20out%20where%20the%20state%20can%20tower%20over%20the%20citizens%2C%20and%20every%20monarchy%20towers%20over%20their%20citizens%2C%20there%E2%80%99s%20no%20doubt%20about%20that.%20But%20the%20sense%20in%20which%20I%20use%20the%20word%20colonial%20is%20a%20continuation%20of%20what%20we%20had%20under%20the%20British.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20Only%20in%20terms%20of%20outline%20structure%2C%20but%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20rights%20that%20were%20infused%20in%2C%20which%20makes%20such%20a%20huge%20difference%2C%20we%20were%20not%20colonial.%20Just%20the%20fact%20that%20they%20borrowed%20the%20structure%20of%20the%201935%20Act%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20really%20mean%20you%20end%20up%20with%20a%20colonial%20document%2C%20because%20the%20contents%20of%20that%20document%20are%20not%20colonial%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EWell%2C%20I%20would%20dispute%20the%20fact%20that%20they%E2%80%99re%20not%20colonial%20at%20all.%20On%20its%20own%2C%20simply%20borrowing%20the%20structure%20is%20not%20colonial%2C%20I%E2%80%99ll%20grant%20that.%20But%20when%20you%20look%20at%20the%20contents%2C%20and%20let%E2%80%99s%20look%20at%20the%20contents.%20Let%E2%80%99s%20look%20at%20a%20specific%20example%3A%20let%E2%80%99s%20look%20at%20the%20right%20to%20life%20and%20personal%20liberty.%20It%20was%20quite%20possible%20for%20the%20framers%20of%20the%20constitution%20to%20write%20that%20everyone%20shall%20have%20a%20right%20to%20life%20and%20personal%20liberty%2C%20full%20stop.%20It%20could%20have%20been%20done%2C%20but%20it%20was%20not%20done.%20Instead%2C%20what%20was%20done%20is%20that%20that%20can%20be%20restricted%20by%20procedure%20established%20by%20law.%20Even%20the%20more%20expansive%20due%20process%20of%20law%2C%20which%20would%20prevent%20the%20state%20from%20taking%20actions%20to%20restrict%20the%20life%20and%20personal%20liberty%20of%20citizens%20was%20not%20done.%20Now%20why%20was%20this%20done%2C%20which%20comes%20back%20to%20the%20unrest%20that%20was%20happening%20at%20that%20time.%20At%20that%20time%2C%20on%20the%209th%20of%20December%20when%20the%20constituent%20assembly%20met%20for%20the%20first%20time%2C%20Mahatma%20Gandhi%20was%20in%20Noakhali%2C%20because%20there%20were%20communal%20rights%20in%20Noakhali.%20So%20it%20was%20in%20their%20minds%20that%20they%20needed%20to%20do%20something%20about%20the%20law%20and%20order%20situation.%20What%20is%20it%20that%20they%20do%3F%20They%20authorise%20preventive%20detention%20in%20the%20constitution.%20Now%20I%20find%20this%20actually%20quite%20incredible%2C%20because%20of%20the%20fact%20that%20we%E2%80%99ve%20all%20heard%20of%20the%20Rowlatt%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F10%2F01131900%2FGandhi_in_Noakhali_1946.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22700%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F10%2F01131900%2FGandhi_in_Noakhali_1946.jpg%20700w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F10%2F01131900%2FGandhi_in_Noakhali_1946-300x220.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-401537%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22514%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EMohandas%20Karamchand%20Gandhi%20in%20Noakhali%2C%201946.%20Photo%3A%20Wikimedia%20Commons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20Let%20me%20put%20it%20like%20this%20%E2%80%93%20there%E2%80%99s%20no%20doubt%20that%20there%20is%20preventive%20detention%20which%20is%20part%20of%20our%20constitution%2C%20there%E2%80%99s%20no%20doubt%20that%20there%20are%20restrictions%20on%20freedom%20of%20speech%20that%20were%20expanded%20with%20the%20First%20Amendment.%20There%20are%20many%20other%20such%2C%20as%20I%20would%20call%20them%20imperfections%20in%20our%20constitution%2C%20but%20to%20conclude%20from%20those%20imperfections%20that%20the%20document%20is%20colonial%20is%20a%20huge%20stretch.%20That%E2%80%99s%20what%20I%E2%80%99m%20questioning.%20You%E2%80%99re%20right%2C%20there%20are%20several%20things%20over%20the%20years%20that%20judges%20have%20watered%20down%20with%20Supreme%20Court%20judgments%20thereafter%2C%20and%20expanded%20the%20right%20to%20life%20and%20interpreted%20it%20in%20multiple%20imaginative%20ways.%20But%20to%20conclude%20from%20the%20facts%20that%20there%20were%20imperfections%20in%20the%20original%20document%2C%20therefore%20it%E2%80%99s%20colonial%20is%20not%20just%20a%20huge%20stretch%2C%20it%20seems%20to%20me%20it%E2%80%99s%20the%20wrong%20application%20of%20the%20word%20colonial.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EWell%20it%20reminds%20me%20of%20the%20famous%20saying%2C%20that%20everything%20you%20say%20in%20India%2C%20the%20opposite%20is%20also%20true.%20I%20think%20it%E2%80%99s%20the%20case%20for%20the%20constitution%20as%20well.%20There%20could%20equally%20be%20a%20book%20called%20%3Ci%3EThe%20Anti-Colonial%20Constitution%3C%2Fi%3E%20and%20that%20would%20be%20true%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EYou%E2%80%99re%20reaching%20a%20point%20where%20you%E2%80%99re%20half%20agreeing%20with%20me%2C%20and%20I%E2%80%99ve%20reached%20a%20point%20where%20I%E2%80%99m%20half%20agreeing%20with%20you.%20I%20think%20this%20is%20a%20fascinating%20discussion%20but%20let%E2%80%99s%20then%20move%20to%20three%20things%20that%20you%20say%20about%20the%20constitution.%20One%20of%20them%20is%20this%20%E2%80%93%20you%20point%20out%20that%20there%20were%20other%20documents%2C%20for%20example%20the%20Hindu%20Mahasabha%20was%20crafting%20a%20constitution%20of%20its%20own%20at%20roughly%20the%20same%20time%2C%20presumably%20in%20competition%20or%20rivalry%20with%20the%20one%20that%20the%20drafting%20committee%20was%20setting%20up.%20But%20what%E2%80%99s%20interesting%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20either%20a%20paradox%20or%20an%20irony%20that%20the%20Hindu%20Mahasabha%20document%20was%20as%20colonial%20as%20the%20one%20that%20we%20ended%20up%20with.%20This%20is%20what%20you%20write%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20substance%20of%20the%20constitution%20of%20the%20Hindustan%20free%20state%20was%20as%20colonially%20inspired%20as%20the%20eventual%20constitution%E2%80%9D.%20How%20do%20you%20explain%20that%2C%20that%20this%20document%20from%20the%20Hindu%20Mahasabha%20et%20all%20being%20colonial%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EI%20think%20the%20interesting%20part%20here%20is%20that%20this%20seems%20like%20a%20paradox%20in%20today%E2%80%99s%20day%20and%20age%2C%20because%20we%20seem%20to%20be%20at%20a%20decolonial%20moment%20with%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20in%20power.%20But%20at%20that%20point%20of%20time%20and%20in%20the%201940s%2C%20the%20established%20wisdom%20particularly%20amongst%20those%20who%20are%20erudite%20lawyers%20who%20end%20up%20drafting%20most%20constitutions%2C%20irrespective%20of%20which%20parties%20drafting%20them%2C%20is%20that%20the%20cutting%20edge%20of%20constitutional%20law%20is%20the%20Anglo-American%20liberal%20model.%20The%20Hindu%20Mahasabha%20is%20no%20exception%2C%20because%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20day%20Savarkar%20is%20a%20complex%20person%20as%20in%20many%20senses%20he%20also%20wants%20India%20to%20be%20a%20modern%20state.%20Savarkar%20himself%20is%20an%20atheist.%20He%20does%20not%20want%20Hinduism%20to%20become%20the%20state%20religion%2C%20so%20he%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20want%20a%20constitution%20that%20is%20pre-modern.%20Who%20has%20suggested%20the%20constitution%3F%20It%20is%20Gandhi%2C%20who%20is%20his%20most%20bitter%20rival.%20So%2C%20in%20some%20sense%2C%20the%20Hindu%20Mahasabha%20suggests%20a%20constitution%20that%20is%20mainstream%20centrist%20and%20reasonable%2C%20because%20it%20wants%20to%20be%20seen%20as%20a%20mainstream%20centrist%20and%20reasonable%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EWhat%20this%20also%20suggests%20is%20that%20whether%20you%20were%20part%20of%20the%20Congress%20or%20the%20Hindu%20Mahasabha%2C%20or%20for%20that%20matter%20even%20the%20Muslim%20League%2C%20their%20inspiration%20for%20the%20constitution%20was%20in%20fact%20the%20values%20from%20the%20French%20Revolution%20onwards%20that%20had%20been%20handed%20down%20and%20accepted%20as%20the%20core%20principles%20of%20democracy%2C%20added%20to%20by%20the%20Americans%20and%20that%20wonderful%20echoing%20phrase%20which%20we%20borrowed%20from%20them%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20the%20people%E2%80%9D.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20that%20western%20influence%2C%20it%20may%20not%20be%20colonial%2C%20but%20that%20western%20influence%20ran%20through%20our%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2017%2F07%2F15155952%2Fhindu-mahasbha.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Group%20photo%20of%20Hindu%20Mahasabha.%20Standing%20-%20Shankar%20Kistaiya%2C%20Gopal%20Godse%2C%20Madanlal%20Pahwa%2C%20Digambar%20Badge.%20Seated%20-%20Narayan%20Apte%2C%20Vinayak%20D.%20Savarkar%2C%20Nathuram%20Godse%2C%20Vishnu%20Karkare.%20Credit%3A%20Flickr%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22625%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-163350%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22584%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EGroup%20photo%20of%20Hindu%20Mahasabha.%20Standing%20%E2%80%93%20Shankar%20Kistaiya%2C%20Gopal%20Godse%2C%20Madanlal%20Pahwa%2C%20Digambar%20Badge.%20Seated%20%E2%80%93%20Narayan%20Apte%2C%20Vinayak%20D.%20Savarkar%2C%20Nathuram%20Godse%2C%20Vishnu%20Karkare.%20Credit%3A%20Flickr%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20That%E2%80%99s%20right%2C%20and%20Ambedkar%20has%20a%20very%20beautiful%20quote%2C%20because%20he%20says%20that%20%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20come%20200%20years%20late%20to%20this%20party.%20Whatever%20had%20to%20happen%20has%20happened%2C%20and%20so%20there%20should%20be%20no%20shame%20in%20copying%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20Absolutely.%20Let%E2%80%99s%20come%20to%20some%20specific%20points%20you%20make%20in%20your%20book%20about%20the%20constitution.%20You%20say%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20Rajya%20Sabha%20remained%20in%20the%20constitution%20of%20India%20because%20it%20was%20tried%20and%20tested%20in%20other%20countries%20as%20a%20means%20of%20preventing%20democracy%20getting%20out%20of%20hand%E2%80%9D.%20But%20look%20at%20the%20way%20the%20Modi%20government%20introduced%20electoral%20bonds%20through%20a%20finance%20act.%20Immediately%20you%20realize%20that%20you%20do%20need%20an%20institution%20like%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20to%20curb%20the%20tendency%20of%20powerful%20prime%20ministers%20like%20Modi%20misusing%20the%20numbers%20they%20have%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha.%20That%E2%80%99s%20really%20why%20you%20need%20a%20Rajya%20Sabha%2C%20which%20may%20not%20have%20been%20apparent%20when%20the%20constitution%20was%20written%20because%20no%20one%20would%20have%20believed%20we%E2%80%99d%20have%20a%20prime%20minister%20who%20would%20steamroll%20electoral%20bonds%20the%20wrong%20way.%20But%20now%20that%20it%E2%80%99s%20been%20done%20you%20suddenly%20realise%20you%20do%20need%20a%20Rajya%20Sabha%2C%20because%20otherwise%20a%20man%20like%20Modi%2C%20and%20I%E2%80%99m%20only%20using%20him%20as%20an%20example%2C%20can%20misuse%20his%20numbers%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20to%20do%20things%20that%20actually%20should%20not%20happen%2C%20in%20a%20way%20they%20shouldn%E2%80%99t%20happen.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20The%20Rajya%20Sabha%20didn%E2%80%99t%20stop%20the%20electoral%20bonds%2C%20Karan%20and%20neither%20did%20it%20stop%20the%2042nd%20Amendment.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20Because%20they%20went%20through%20a%20finance%20act.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20They%20didn%E2%80%99t%20stop%20the%2042nd%20Amendment%20during%20Indira%20Gandhi%E2%80%99s%20time.%20I%20think%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20is%20only%20in%20theory%20a%20check%20on%20elected%20government.%20I%20think%20in%20concept%20it%20seems%20nice%2C%20it%20makes%20us%20feel%20good%20about%20ourselves%20but%20it%20actually%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20work.%20So%20if%20we%20really%20want%20to%20look%20at%20curbing%20an%20elected%20government%20%E2%80%93%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20No.%20The%20Rajya%20Sabha%2C%20often%20when%20the%20government%20of%20the%20day%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20have%20a%20majority%2C%20there%20is%20a%20check%20on%20the%20sort%20of%20legislation%20the%20government%20can%20bring.%20We%20know%20that%20from%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20experience%20in%20the%20last%20eight%20years%20%E2%80%93%20he%E2%80%99s%20often%20had%20to%20be%20careful%20about%20what%20he%20does.%20His%20attempt%20to%20pass%20the%20first%20labor%20reforms%20in%20the%20first%20year%2C%20they%20were%20checked%20because%20he%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20get%20the%20land%20acquisition%20through%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EThat%E2%80%99s%20right.%20I%20think%20that%20yes%2C%20there%20obviously%20can%20be%20cases%20where%20there%20is%20a%20check%20and%20balance%2C%20but%20I%20actually%20dispute%20this%20premise.%20My%20view%20is%20that%20as%20a%20nation%2C%20we%20are%20only%20as%20good%20as%20the%20people%20we%20elect.%20If%20the%20people%20we%20elect%20are%20people%20whom%20we%20think%20are%20unfit%2C%20then%20we%20have%20the%20power%20of%20the%20ballot%20to%20vote%20them%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F02%2F08191441%2F2022_2img08_Feb_2022_PTI02_08_2022_000083B.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F02%2F08191441%2F2022_2img08_Feb_2022_PTI02_08_2022_000083B.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F02%2F08191441%2F2022_2img08_Feb_2022_PTI02_08_2022_000083B-300x151.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F02%2F08191441%2F2022_2img08_Feb_2022_PTI02_08_2022_000083B-1024x514.jpg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F02%2F08191441%2F2022_2img08_Feb_2022_PTI02_08_2022_000083B-800x400.jpg%20800w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-580348%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22602%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPrime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20speaks%20in%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha.%20Photo%3A%20RSTV%20grab%20via%20PTI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3ENot%20that%20they%20are%20unfit%2C%20although%20that%20may%20follow%3B%20but%20that%20if%20you%20give%20people%20such%20huge%20power%2C%20they%20will%20have%20a%20tendency%20to%20abuse%20it.%20All%20power%20corrupts%2C%20absolute%20power%20corrupts.%20When%20a%20man%20or%20a%20prime%20minister%20has%20a%20number%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20where%20he%20can%20do%20whatever%20he%20wants%2C%20that%E2%80%99s%20when%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%2C%20if%20he%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20have%20a%20majority%20becomes%20an%20effective%20check.%20It%E2%80%99s%20not%20a%20way%20of%20throttling%20democracy%20%E2%80%93%20it%20then%20becomes%20a%20way%20of%20ensuring%20there%E2%80%99s%20no%20abusive%20democracy.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EYeah%2C%20and%20I%20think%20that%20was%20very%20much%20the%20thinking%20as%20with%20the%20constituent%20assembly.%20As%20I%20said%20and%20I%20may%20sound%20like%20a%20broken%20record%20here%2C%20the%20fact%20is%20that%20I%20think%20that%20if%20a%20prime%20minister%20has%20been%20voted%20in%20by%20such%20a%20landslide%20majority%2C%20and%20if%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20like%20what%20they%20are%20doing%2C%20then%20we%20can%20vote%20the%20prime%20minister%20out.%20I%20think%20these%20checks%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20or%20you%20know%20legal%20checks%20in%20terms%20of%20High%20Court%20striking%20it%20down%20can%20be%20edge%20cases%2C%20they%20are%20marginal%20cases%2C%20but%20I%20think%20ultimately%20we%20shouldn%E2%80%99t%20feel%20comfortable%20that%20there%20is%20some%20other%20institution%20that%E2%80%99s%20doing%20the%20job%20for%20us.%20It%E2%80%99s%20not.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20All%20right%2C%20that%E2%80%99s%20a%20disputable%20point%20but%20let%E2%80%99s%20come%20to%20the%20second%20one.%20I%E2%80%99ll%20give%20you%20another%20example%3A%20you%20say%2C%20%E2%80%9COnly%20a%20constitution%20that%20does%20not%20trust%20its%20legislators%20has%20to%20lay%20down%20an%20excruciating%20detail%20of%20what%20rules%20of%20procedure%20they%20must%20adopt%E2%80%9D.%20Once%20again%2C%20look%20at%20the%20record%20of%20the%20Modi%20government.%20I%E2%80%99ll%20point%20out%20again%20that%20I%E2%80%99m%20only%20using%20it%20as%20an%20example.%20They%E2%80%99ve%20run%20rough%20shots%20over%20procedures%20right%20through%20nine%20years%2C%20which%20is%20why%20when%20the%20constitution%20lays%20down%20in%20what%20you%20call%20%E2%80%9Cexcruciating%20detail%E2%80%9D%2C%20how%20they%20must%20be%20followed.%20The%20constitution%20is%20hoping%20to%20tell%20people%20as%20powerful%20as%20Modi%2C%20%E2%80%9CLook%2C%20there%20are%20ways%20of%20doing%20things%2C%20the%20means%20are%20as%20important%20as%20the%20end%2C%20the%20right%20means%20are%20necessary%E2%80%9D.%20It%E2%80%99s%20only%20if%20you%20lay%20it%20down%20in%20that%20way%2C%20that%20a%20man%20with%20the%20power%20of%20Modi%20is%20hopefully%20encouraged%20to%20fulfil%20the%20procedure.%20Even%20then%20he%20violates%20it%2C%20but%20at%20least%20the%20constitution%20making%20an%20effort%20to%20tell%20procedure%20is%20important.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20I%20just%20feel%20that%20this%20cannot%20happen%20by%20dictation.%20This%20is%20something%20that%20is%20a%20culture%20of%20compliance%20with%20law%2C%20which%20cannot%20happen%20because%20the%20constitution%20is%20saying%20in%20some%20painful%20detail%20as%20to%20how%20a%20bill%20is%20to%20be%20introduced.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20But%20then%20the%20corollary%20to%20what%20you%E2%80%99re%20saying%20is%20that%20the%20culture%20of%20compliance%20with%20law%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20exist%20in%20the%20Modi%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3C%2Fb%3E%3A%20I%20think%20this%20is%20a%20much%20larger%20case%2C%20because%20I%20think%20that%20we%20shouldn%E2%80%99t%20fall%20into%20the%20trap%20of%20seeing%20this%20through%20Modi%20tinted%20glasses.%20I%20think%20that%20there%20is%20a%20problem%20with%20the%20culture%20of%20compliance%20of%20law%2C%20written%20law%20in%20the%20way%20in%20which%20we%20think%20of%20law%20in%20the%20country%20generally.%20I%20know%20this%20is%20a%20large%20game.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EBut%20then%20you%E2%80%99re%20giving%20a%20second%20good%20reason%20as%20to%20why%20the%20constitution%20spelled%20it%20out%20in%20excruciating%20detail.%20The%20framers%20must%20have%20been%20aware%20of%20what%20you%E2%80%99re%20talking%20about%2C%20that%20the%20culture%20of%20compliance%20with%20law%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20exist%20in%20India%2C%20therefore%20we%20must%20spread%20in%20detail%20the%20procedures%20that%20must%20be%20followed.%20Otherwise%2C%20because%20that%20culture%20of%20compliance%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20exist%2C%20people%20will%20deliberately%20short%20circuit%2C%20people%20will%20deliberately%20take%20shortcuts.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EI%20think%2C%20and%20this%20may%20sound%20very%20counterintuitive%2C%20but%20the%20fact%20that%20there%20is%20no%20culture%20of%20compliance%20means%20that%20you%20cannot%20impose%20a%20culture%20of%20compliance%20by%20writing%20densely.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EYou%20can%20certainly%20try.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20I%20mean%20that%E2%80%99s%20what%20they%20did%2C%20that%20was%20very%20much%20the%20effort.%20This%20is%20sort%20of%20maybe%20much%20more%20Gandhian%20in%20this%20way%2C%20but%20I%20would%20say%20that%20we%20have%20to%20wait%20for%20our%20time.%20This%20culture%20of%20compliance%20will%20grow%2C%20the%20sense%20of%20responsibility%20will%20grow.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20But%20then%20what%E2%80%99s%20the%20point%20of%20the%20constitution%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EThe%20constitution%20serves%20as%20a%20framework%2C%20but%20as%20to%20how%20a%20bill%20will%20be%20introduced%2C%20some%20conventions%20will%20develop%2C%20so%20let%20conventions%20develop.%20What%20happens%20when%20you%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20conventions%20developed%2C%20is%20that%20you%20spell%20out%20everything%20in%20detail%20and%20then%20nothing%20is%20left%20for%20convention.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EThere%20is%20a%20view%2C%20that%20in%20fact%20one%20of%20the%20things%20the%20constitution%20did%20was%20actually%20to%20create%20a%20democracy%2C%20and%20to%20create%20the%20spirit%20and%20culture%20of%20democracy%20that%20didn%E2%80%99t%20exist%20earlier.%20That%E2%80%99s%20another%20reason%20why%20things%20have%20to%20be%20spelled%20out%2C%20because%20the%20constitution%20was%20actually%20creating%20the%20Indian%20people%20in%20the%20mold.%20It%20wanted%20them%20to%20follow%2C%20rather%20than%20the%20opposite.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20I%20dispute%20this%20view%2C%20while%20I%20agree%20with%20parts%20of%20this%20thesis.%20But%20the%20general%20thesis%2C%20and%20Madhav%20Khosla%20has%20written%20a%20book%20called%20%3Ci%3EThe%20Founding%20Moment%3C%2Fi%3E%20which%20you%20know%20%E2%80%93%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20That%E2%80%99s%20exactly%20what%20I%E2%80%99m%20talking%20about.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20That%E2%80%99s%20the%20thesis.%20I%20think%20it%20is%20something%20that%20I%20would%20like%20to%20dispute%2C%20that%20the%20constitution%20created%20the%20Indian%20people.%20The%20constitution%20created%20the%20Indian%20people%20only%20in%20a%20legal%20sense.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EI%20think%20what%20he%20meant%20is%20the%20constitution%20created%20the%20Indian%20people%20in%20a%20democratic%20sense.%20The%20cultural%20compliance%20that%20you%20say%20didn%E2%80%99t%20exist%2C%20the%20constitution%20sought%20to%20try%20and%20create.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3C%2Fb%3E%3A%20No.%20I%20think%20that%20the%20culture%20of%20democracy%20in%20India%20starts%20with%20our%20freedom%20movement%2C%20and%20not%20the%20constitution.%20It%20starts%20with%20protesting%20against%20colonial%20rule%20and%20not%20the%20constitution.%20This%20is%20what%20I%20find%20quite%20interesting%2C%20and%20I%20write%20it%20in%20my%20book%20as%20well%2C%20that%20the%20culmination%20of%20the%20freedom%20movement%20and%20the%20Constitution%20are%20happening%20contemporaneously%2C%20but%20it%20seems%20like%20they%E2%80%99re%20happening%20in%20two%20different%20worlds.%20The%20freedom%20movement%20is%20all%20about%20non-violence%20and%20satyagraha%3B%20the%20words%20%E2%80%98non-violence%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98satyagraha%E2%80%99%20don%E2%80%99t%20find%20any%20mention%20in%20the%20constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EI%20think%20in%20your%20introduction%20or%20prologue%20you%20explicitly%20say%20the%20word%20%E2%80%98non-violence%E2%80%99%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20exist%20in%20the%20constitution%20at%20all%2C%20and%20yet%20that%20was%20the%20central%20mantra%20of%20the%20freedom%20movement.%20Why%20does%20the%20absence%20of%20the%20word%20%E2%80%98non-violence%E2%80%99%20make%20the%20constitution%20colonial%2C%20and%20how%20would%20that%20world%20have%20fitted%20in%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20You%E2%80%99re%20right%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20really%20the%20absence%20of%20the%20word%20because%20that%20would%20be%20a%20very%20simplistic%20claim%20to%20make%2C%20but%20it%E2%80%99s%20almost%20as%20if%20the%20spirit%20of%20the%20freedom%20movement%20had%20evaporated%20by%20the%20time%20the%20framers%20of%20the%20constitution%20came%20into%20the%20constituent%20assembly.%20Shankarrao%20Deo-%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20The%20spirit%20of%20the%20freedom%20movement%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20simply%20encapsulated%20with%20the%20word%20%E2%80%98non-violence%E2%80%99.%20The%20spirit%20of%20the%20freedom%20movement%20was%20also%20to%20create%20a%20modern%2C%20free%2C%20independent%20state%20that%20would%20allow%20Indian%20people%20to%20fulfill%20their%20potential%20that%20would%20give%20them%20the%20freedoms%20and%20the%20rights%20they%20didn%E2%80%99t%20have%2C%20that%20would%20give%20them%20a%20democratic%20structure%20which%20they%20didn%E2%80%99t%20have.%20All%20of%20that%20was%20fulfilled%20in%20the%20constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20In%20the%20broader%20sense%2C%20the%20constitution%20had%20one%20thing%20going%20for%20it%20%E2%80%93%20which%20was%20exactly%20echoing%20what%20the%20freedom%20movement%20did%2C%20the%20spirit%20of%20tolerance%20and%20consensus.%20Yes%2C%20it%20was%20a%20constitution%20that%20came%20about%20through%20great%20consensus%2C%20which%20is%20what%20the%20freedom%20movement%20was%20aspiring%20to%20do.%20But%2C%20the%20text%20of%20the%20constitution%20did%20not%20echo%20that%20vision.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20Let%20me%20raise%20one%20third%20point%20that%20you%20make%2C%20and%20I%E2%80%99ll%20be%20honest%20with%20you%2C%20I%20find%20this%20particularly%20bizarre.%20Right%20at%20the%20end%20of%20your%20book%2C%20you%20argue%20that%20the%20treatment%20of%20daily%20wage%20workers%20during%20the%20lockdown%20when%20they%20were%20having%20to%20walk%20hundreds%20if%20not%20thousands%20of%20miles%20back%20to%20their%20villages%2C%20is%20somehow%20proof%20that%20the%20constitution%20is%20colonial.%20You%20write%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20indignity%20of%20being%20made%20to%20squat%20in%20public%20and%20then%20forcibly%20made%20to%20bathe%20in%20disinfectant%2C%20captured%20in%20one%20image%20the%20reality%20of%20the%20colonial%20constitution.%20It%20had%20shown%20its%20true%20colours%20in%20Bareilly%20in%202020%E2%80%9D.%20That%E2%80%99s%20simply%20not%20true.%20What%20happened%20in%20barely%20in%202020%2C%20was%20a%20breach%20of%20the%20constitution%20%E2%80%93%20it%20was%20disregard%20of%20the%20constitution%2C%20it%20was%20defiance%20of%20the%20constitution%20by%20a%20high-handed%20Yogi%20Adityanath%20government%20with%20a%20brute%20majority%20in%20the%20assembly.%20It%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20a%20result%20of%20the%20constitution%2C%20it%20was%20undermining%20the%20constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20I%20think%20that%E2%80%99s%20a%20simplistic%20reading%20Karan%2C%20because%20my%20sense%20is%20that%20the%20state%20towered%20above%20the%20citizens.%20The%20reason%20I%20picked%20that%20example%20is%20because%20it%20was%20very%20graphic%2C%20and%20we%E2%80%99ve%20all%20seen%20that.%20When%20there%20are%2050%20labourers%20sitting%20on%20their%20haunches%20and%20then%20there%E2%80%99s%20an%20officer%20who%E2%80%99s%20spraying%20them%20with%20chemical%20disinfectant%2C%20I%20felt%20ashamed%20as%20an%20Indian%20on%20that%20day%20when%20I%20saw%20that%20photo.%20The%20reason%20as%20to%20why%20we%20are%20in%20this%20situation%2C%20and%20I%20say%20this%20with%20great%20humility%2C%20is%20that%20the%20constitution%20didn%E2%80%99t%20do%20enough%2C%20which%20is%20why%20our%20governments%20can%20behave%20like%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F04%2F17025436%2Fspray-1186458354-1585572377.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F04%2F17025436%2Fspray-1186458354-1585572377.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F04%2F17025436%2Fspray-1186458354-1585572377-300x146.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F04%2F17025436%2Fspray-1186458354-1585572377-1024x498.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-523068%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22584%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20infamous%20incident%20from%20March%2030%2C%202020%2C%20when%20healthcare%20workers%2C%20in%20protective%20suits%2C%20used%20a%20hosepipe%20to%20spray%20disinfectant%20on%20migrant%20workers%20before%20allowing%20them%20to%20enter%20the%20town%20of%20Bareilly.%20Photo%3A%20PTI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EHad%20this%20matter%20been%20taken%20to%20court%2C%20it%20would%20have%20been%20struck%20down%20immediately%20and%20the%20judges%20would%20have%20condemned%20the%20government%20for%20doing%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EOn%20what%20ground%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EOn%20the%20grounds%20that%20you%20are%20treating%20people%20as%20if%20they%20are%20slaves%20and%20animals%2C%20breaching%20their%20rights%20of%20freedom%2C%20equality%20and%20liberty.%20All%20of%20those%20would%20have%20stood%20up%20in%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20Yes%20but%20this%20matter%20was%20taken%20to%20court.%20The%20last%20I%20know%2C%20there%20has%20been%20no%20judgment%20on%20this%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20Let%20me%20tell%20you%20something.%20That%20is%20not%20a%20reflection%20of%20the%20constitution%2C%20that%20is%20the%20reflection%20of%20the%20judges%20interpreting%20the%20constitution%20and%20the%20alacrity%20and%20diligence%20with%20which%20they%20do%20the%20work.%20I%20mean%2C%20you%20can%20have%20a%20great%20constitution%20which%20is%20not%20colonial%2C%20but%20judges%20who%20failed%20to%20act%2C%20who%20deliberately%20kicked%20the%20ball%20down%20the%20road%2C%20who%20come%20up%20with%20perverse%20judgments%2C%20that%E2%80%99s%20not%20a%20reflection%20of%20the%20constitution%20%E2%80%93%20that%E2%80%99s%20a%20reflection%20on%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EAbsolutely.%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20want%20to%20give%20any%20judge%20who%20is%20not%20doing%20their%20duty%20or%20a%20government%20which%20has%20behaved%20in%20this%20manner%2C%20a%20free%20pass.%20Of%20course%20they%20are%20to%20blame%20and%20there%E2%80%99s%20no%20doubt%20about%20that.%20But%20I%20think%20in%20India%20we%E2%80%99ve%20got%20this%20very%20convenient%20expression%2C%20that%20%E2%80%98We%20have%20enough%20laws%20which%20are%20good%2C%20but%20they%20are%20not%20implemented%E2%80%99.%20I%20think%20it%E2%80%99s%20time%20to%20think%20about%20the%20laws%20as%20well%20%E2%80%93%20why%20is%20it%20that%20we%20are%20in%20a%20situation%20where%20governments%20and%20judges%20can%20do%20this%20and%20get%20away%20with%20it%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EWhich%20law%20would%20have%20permitted%20governments%20to%20bathe%20people%20having%20made%20them%20squat%20on%20the%20road%20with%20disinfectant%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20I%20think%20that%20this%20is%20exactly%20the%20kind%20of%20large%20moral%20question%20which%20a%20constitution%20is%20meant%20to%20understand.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20No%20constitutional%20framework%2C%20whether%20in%202023%20or%201949%20would%20have%20asked%20themselves%20the%20question%20%E2%80%98How%20do%20I%20cater%20for%20a%20situation%20where%20a%20man%20like%20Yogi%20Adityanath%20will%20make%20people%20squat%20on%20the%20road%20and%20bathe%20them%20with%20disinfectant%3F%E2%80%99%20That%E2%80%99s%20not%20something%20constitution%20makers%20didn%E2%80%99t%20think%20about.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20They%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20be%20able%20to%20think%20of%20the%20example%2C%20but%20they%20can%20certainly%20think%20about%20the%20right%20to%20life%20with%20dignity%20being%20completely%20untrammelled.%20I%20think%20this%20is%20something%20that%20that%20can%20be%20thought%20about%20by%20a%20constitutional%20framer%2C%20and%20I%20remember%20what%20Chief%20Justice%20John%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20You%E2%80%99re%20saying%20the%20absence%20of%20the%20right%20to%20life%20completely%20untrammelled%20means%20the%20constitution%20becomes%20colonial%3F%20That%E2%80%99s%20a%20huge%20jump.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20That%E2%80%99s%20a%20bit%20reductionist.%20I%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20say%20that%2C%20but%20the%20constitution%20gives%20the%20state%20huge%20powers%2C%20and%20every%20government%20knows%20that%20and%20that%20is%20what%20they%20use.%20If%20I%20could%20give%20you%20one%20statistic%2C%20because%20I%20found%20this%20quite%20incredible%2C%20some%20of%20my%20colleagues%20at%20Vidhi%20Center%20have%20come%20up%20with%20this%20%E2%80%93%20in%202021%2C%2058%20lakh%20people%20were%20arrested%20in%20India.%20These%20are%20people%20who%20are%20arrested%20by%20following%20the%20procedures%20of%20the%20IPC.%20The%20number%20of%20people%20who%20have%20been%20detained%2C%20that%20is%20without%20a%20legal%20process%2C%20is%2086.6%20lakhs.%20There%20are%2087%20lakh%20people%20who%20have%20been%20detained%2C%20which%20is%20essentially%20a%20policeman%20going%2C%20picking%20somebody%20up%20and%20putting%20them%20in%20lock%20up%20for%20a%20day%20or%20two%2C%20because%20they%20don%E2%80%99t%20want%20them%20to%20breach%20law%20and%20order%20or%20because%20they%20just%20don%E2%80%99t%20like%20the%20look%20of%20their%20face.%20Now%2C%20this%20is%20the%20country%20that%20we%20live%20in.%20It%20will%20not%20happen%2C%20in%20all%20likelihood%2C%20to%20people%20sitting%20in%20Lutyens%20Delhi%2C%20it%20will%20not%20happen%20to%20people%20sitting%20in%20South%20Bombay%2C%20but%20it%20is%20going%20to%20happen%20to%20people%20who%20aren%E2%80%99t%20that%20fortunate%20%E2%80%93%20and%20that%20is%20the%20state%20we%20are%20in%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EBut%20to%20jump%20from%20that%2C%20and%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20despicable%20situation%20you%20describe.%20By%20no%20means%20would%20I%20justify%20what%E2%80%99s%20happening.%20But%20to%20jump%20from%20that%20to%20the%20conclusion%20that%20the%20constitution%20is%20colonial%20is%20like%20saying%20that%20what%20happened%20in%20America%20in%20the%2050s%20against%20communists%2C%20which%20was%20illegal%20and%20wrong%2C%20means%20that%20the%20American%20constitution%20is%20colonial.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%3C%2Fb%3ENo%2C%20I%20think%20that%20we%20have%20to%20look%20at%20who%20is%20responsible%2C%20and%20responsibility%20goes%20all%20the%20way.%20While%20certainly%20for%20something%20of%20this%20nature%2C%20the%20responsibility%20starts%20with%20the%20police%20officer%20who%20is%20not%20doing%20their%20duty%2C%20and%20goes%20right%20up%20to%20a%20framer%20of%20the%20constitution%20who%20is%20unable%20to%20think%20of%20what%20India%20would%20be%20like%20100%20years%20later.%20Because%20as%20I%20was%20saying%2C%20since%20you%20gave%20the%20American%20example%2C%20Chief%20Justice%20John%20Marshall%20of%20the%20United%20States%20had%20a%20very%20good%20quote%2C%20which%20is%20that%20%E2%80%9CWhen%20we%20are%20interpreting%20the%20constitution%2C%20we%20must%20always%20remember%20it%20is%20the%20constitution%20we%20are%20expounding%E2%80%9D.%20It%20is%20something%20that%20is%20for%20all%20times%20to%20come%2C%20and%20not%20an%20immediate%20expedient%20for%20today.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20Let%20me%20put%20it%20like%20this%3A%20your%20argument%20reminds%20me%20of%20the%20following%2C%20which%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20think%20most%20people%20agree%20with%20%E2%80%93%20Trump%E2%80%99s%20failure%20to%20prevent%20what%20happened%20on%20January%20the%206th%202021%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20mean%20that%20the%20constitution%20of%20America%20endorsed%20it%20and%20permitted%20it%20to%20happen.%20Similarly%2C%20the%20failure%20of%20a%20judge%20to%20act%2C%20the%20failure%20of%20a%20police%20officer%20to%20go%20down%20to%20the%20bottom%2C%20or%20the%20prime%20minister%20to%20go%20to%20the%20top%20to%20act%2C%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20mean%20the%20constitution%20is%20to%20blame.%20Those%20individuals%20are%20to%20blame.%20Just%20as%20Trump%20is%20to%20blame%20and%20not%20the%20American%20constitution%2C%20Modi%20or%20the%20policemen%20or%20judges%20are%20to%20blame%2C%20not%20the%20constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EI%20mean%20blame%20is%20a%20strong%20word%20but%20as%20I%20said%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EResponsible%2C%20then.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EAs%20I%20say%2C%20that%20it%20is%20a%20time%20for%20some%20introspection.%20We%20can%E2%80%99t%20simply%20say%20and%20I%20think%20it%20makes%20us%20feel%20comfortable%20to%20say%20that%20%E2%80%9COh%20that%20policeman%20is%20not%20doing%20their%20duty%E2%80%9D.%20Yes%2C%20that%20policeman%20isn%E2%80%99t%20doing%20their%20duty%2C%20but%20I%20think%20we%20have%20to%20ask%20that%20question%20%E2%80%93%20why%20is%20he%20or%20she%20not%20doing%20her%20duty%3F%20I%20think%20that%20goes%20up%20all%20the%20way%2C%20as%20in%20right%20through%20all%20chief%20ministers%20and%20prime%20ministers%2C%20right%20up%20the%20way%20all%20the%20way%20to%20what%20is%20the%20governing%20mechanism%20in%20India.%20I%20think%20it%E2%80%99s%20certainly%20food%20for%20thought%20to%20see%20as%20to%20can%20the%20constitution%20do%20something%20about%20this%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EDidn%E2%80%99t%20Ambedkar%20have%20something%20to%20say%20about%20this%3F%20No%20matter%20how%20bad%20a%20constitution%2C%20if%20good%20people%20implement%20it%2C%20it%20will%20be%20good.%20He%20said%20the%20opposite%20%E2%80%93%20no%20matter%20how%20good%20a%20constitution%2C%20if%20bad%20people%20implement%20it%2C%20it%20will%20be%20bad.%20We%20have%20a%20situation%20in%20India%20where%20progressively%20bad%20to%20worse%20people%20are%20implementing%20it%20at%20all%20levels%2C%20which%20is%20why%20people%20begin%20to%20raise%20questions%20about%20the%20constitution.%20Which%20is%20why%20your%20conclusion%20is%20colonial%2C%20and%20I%E2%80%99m%20saying%20to%20you%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20colonial%2C%20but%20yes%20bad%20people%20going%20to%20worse%20are%20implementing%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20That%E2%80%99s%20right.%20I%20think%2C%20because%20you%20gave%20the%20American%20example%2C%20the%20American%20constitution%20is%20based%20on%20the%20idea%20that%20people%20will%20be%20bad.%20I%20think%20every%20constitutional%20framework%2C%20unless%20they%20are%20overly%20optimistic%2C%20will%20know%20that%20the%20people%20who%20implement%20the%20constitution%20will%20do%20it%20for%20their%20own%20selfish%20devices.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EYou%E2%80%99re%20saying%20the%20framers%20of%20the%20Indian%20constitution%20didn%E2%80%99t%20realise%20how%20terrible%20the%20Indian%20people%20would%20turn%20out%20to%20be%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20No%2C%20and%20I%20think%20that%20this%20is%20something%20I%20must%20say%20with%20all%20humility%2C%20that%20this%20is%20what%20was%20expected.%20The%20only%20person%20who%20knew%20that%20this%20would%20happen%20but%20cast%20it%20positively%2C%20was%20Gandhi%20%E2%80%93%20because%20Gandhi%20said%20that%20what%20we%20actually%20need%20is%20not%20so%20much%20a%20legal%20text.%20He%20said%2C%20%E2%80%98A%20son%20cannot%20follow%20their%20father%20as%20a%20matter%20of%20policy%2C%20or%20a%20matter%20of%20law%E2%80%99.%20What%20it%20needs%20is%20moral%20regeneration.%20I%20think%20that%20he%20was%20onto%20something