%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20I%20mean%20that%E2%80%99s%20because%20of%20the%20starting%20point%20that%20they%20had.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20That%E2%80%99s%20a%20dewy-eyed%20view%20of%20the%20Indian%20people%2C%20needlessly%20good%20and%20kind%20and%20generous%20to%20them%2C%20whereas%20they%20shouldn%E2%80%99t%20have%20been.%20But%20let%20me%20end%20with%20what%20I%20think%20is%20very%20interesting%2C%20and%20this%20is%20literally%20my%20last%20question.%20Despite%20your%20criticism%20of%20the%20constitution%2C%20you%20are%20not%20calling%20for%20a%20new%20constitution.%20You%20write%2C%20%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20not%20a%20call%20to%20draft%20a%20new%20constitution%20today.%20We%20live%20in%20polarised%20times%2C%20and%20any%20constitution%20that%20emerges%20after%20such%20a%20time%20is%20unlikely%20to%20be%20long%20lasting%E2%80%9D.%20So%20you%20would%20fundamentally%20disagree%20with%20the%20Chairman%20of%20the%20Prime%20Minister%E2%80%99s%20Economic%20Advisory%20Council%2C%20Bibek%20Debroy%2C%20who%20recently%20wrote%20an%20article%20in%20%3Ci%3EMint%3C%2Fi%3E%20calling%20for%20a%20new%20constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FlaWeb3Qqq_k%3Ffeature%3Doembed%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22840%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22We%20Have%20Veiled%20Emergency%2C%20Judges%20Often%20Lack%20Spine%2C%20Writing%20New%20Constitution%20at%20This%20Time%20Impossible%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22473%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EIf%20the%20question%20is%20one%20of%20timing%2C%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20think%20this%20is%20a%20time%20to%20write%20a%20new%20constitution.%20It%E2%80%99s%20not%20at%20all%2C%20because%20if%20we%20have%20some%20ideas%20that%20we%20think%20will%20serve%20India%20better%20then%20we%20need%20consensus%20on%20those%20ideas.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20And%20that%E2%80%99s%20missing%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EConsensus%20is%20completely%20missing%20from%20the%20political%20spectrum%20today%2C%20and%20that%E2%80%99s%20number%20one.%20But%20that%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20mean%20that%20we%20have%20these%20banal%20homilies%20towards%20the%20constitution%2C%20that%20it%E2%80%99s%20working%20beautifully%20for%20us%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20only%20the%20people%20that%E2%80%99s%20the%20problem.%20I%20think%20that%20India%20does%20need%2C%20as%20I%E2%80%99ve%20said%20in%20the%20book%2C%20to%20discuss%20new%20constitutional%20ideas.%20There%20are%20simplistic%20ways%20in%20which%20one%20needs%20to%20discuss%20it.%20There%20is%20a%20export%20duty%20waiver%20for%20West%20Bengal%2C%20Bihar%20and%20Orissa%20for%20export%20of%20jute%3B%20those%20things%20need%20to%20go.%20There%20are%20some%20parts%20of%20the%20constitution%20that%20simply%20are%20not%20needed%2C%20and%20there%20are%20other%20parts%20of%20the%20constitution%20like%20preventive%20detention%2C%20like%20the%20heavy%20centralisation%20which%20I%20think%20with%20the%20wisdom%20of%2075%20years%20needs%20to%20be%20rethought.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EIt%20sounds%20to%20me%20like%20what%20you%E2%80%99re%20saying%20is%20that%20there%20are%20things%20in%20the%20constitution%20that%20need%20to%20be%20corrected%2C%20others%20that%20need%20to%20be%20improved%2C%20and%20some%20that%20need%20to%20be%20amended.%20That%20is%20different%20from%20saying%20we%20need%20a%20new%20constitution.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20The%20question%20of%20a%20new%20constitution%20is%20always%20a%20political%20one%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20really%20a%20question%20that%20is%20a%20legal%20question.%20Now%20whether%20it%20is%20a%20new%20constitution%2C%20whether%20it%20is%20a%20constitutional%20amendment%2C%20what%20form%20it%20takes%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20know.%20But%20I%20do%20think%20that%20we%20need%20to%20discuss%20new%20constitutional%20ideas.%20Do%20we%20want%20a%20new%20constitution%20overnight%3F%20Absolutely%20not.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20We%20always%20need%20to%20discuss%20new%20constitutional%20ideas.%20We%20always%20need%20to%20discuss%20ways%20in%20which%20we%20expand%20the%20freedoms%20and%20rights%20that%20we%20have%2C%20and%20we%20always%20need%20to%20discuss%20how%20we%20ensure%20that%20those%20who%20are%20charged%20with%20defending%20them%20and%20implementing%20them%20become%20better%20at%20it%2C%20and%20don%E2%80%99t%20actually%20abuse%20them%20at%20the%20cost%20of%20the%20rights%20of%20the%20citizens.%20I%20agree%20with%20you%20then.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EExactly.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EThank%20you%20very%20much%20indeed.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EArghya%20Sengupta%3A%20%3C%2Fb%3EThank%20you%2C%20Karan.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696240823000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F02141920%2FScreenshot-2023-10-02-at-2.18.13.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Ffull-text-transcript-karan-thapar-arghya-sengupta-colonial-constitution%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Is%20India's%20constitution%20colonial%3F%20Or%20is%20it%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20the%20opposite%3F%20Karan%20Thapar%20questions%20Arghya%20Sengupta's%20views%20on%20the%20matter%20in%20this%20lively%20interview.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Ffull-text-transcript-karan-thapar-arghya-sengupta-colonial-constitution%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22As%20Law%20Commission%20Recommends%20Against%20Lowering%20Age%20of%20Consent%2C%20Questions%20on%20Stigma%20of%20Criminalisation%20Remain%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F02142709%2Fpexels-cottonbro-studio-4631064.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Law%20Commission%20of%20India%20has%20recommended%20to%20the%20Union%20government%20that%20the%20existing%20age%20of%20consent%2C%20which%20is%2018%2C%20should%20not%20be%20tinkered%20with%20under%20the%20Protection%20of%20Children%20from%20Sexual%20Offences%20Act%20(POCSO)%2C%202012%20citing%20the%20dangers%20of%20child%20abuse%2C%20trafficking%20and%20prostitution.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CAfter%20a%20careful%20review%20of%20existing%20child%20protection%20laws%2C%20various%20judgments%20and%20considering%20the%20maladies%20of%20child%20abuse%2C%20child%20trafficking%20and%20child%20prostitution%20that%20plague%20our%20society%2C%20the%20Commission%20is%20of%20the%20measured%20view%20that%20it%20is%20not%20advisable%20to%20tinker%20with%20the%20existing%20age%20of%20consent%20under%20the%20POCSO%20Act%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20the%20report.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20283rd%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdnbbsr.s3waas.gov.in%2Fs3ca0daec69b5adc880fb464895726dbdf%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F20230929466194485.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ereport%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20of%20the%20law%20commission%20headed%20by%20Justice%20Ritu%20Raj%20Awasthi%20titled%20%E2%80%9CAge%20of%20Consent%20under%20the%20Protection%20of%20Children%20from%20Sexual%20Offences%20Act%2C%202012%E2%80%9D%20was%20released%20on%20Friday%20and%20has%20been%20submitted%20to%20the%20Union%20minister%20for%20law%20and%20justice%20Arjun%20Ram%20Meghwal.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20report%20has%20also%20recommended%20to%20the%20law%20ministry%20that%20certain%20amendments%20need%20to%20be%20brought%20in%20the%20POCSO%20Act%20and%20introduce%20judicial%20discretion%20%E2%80%9Cto%20remedy%20the%20situation%20in%20cases%20wherein%20there%20is%20tacit%20approval%20in%20fact%20though%20not%20consent%20in%20law%20on%20part%20of%20the%20child%20aged%20between%2016%20to%2018%20years.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20so%20because%20in%20our%20considered%20opinion%2C%20such%20cases%20do%20not%20merit%20to%20be%20dealt%20with%20the%20same%20severity%20as%20the%20cases%20that%20were%20ideally%20imagined%20to%20fall%20under%20the%20POCSO%20Act.%20The%20Commission%2C%20therefore%2C%20deems%20it%20fit%20to%20introduce%20guided%20judicial%20discretion%20in%20the%20matter%20of%20sentencing%20in%20such%20cases.%20This%20will%20ensure%20that%20the%20law%20is%20balanced%2C%20thus%20safeguarding%20the%20best%20interests%20of%20the%20child%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20commission%20said%20it%20had%20received%20a%20reference%20from%20the%20Karnataka%20high%20court%20(Dharwad%20bench)%20to%20look%20at%20the%20age%20criteria%20for%20consent%2C%20taking%20into%20consideration%20the%20rising%20number%20of%20cases%20relating%20to%20minor%20girls%20above%20the%20age%20of%2016%20years%20falling%20in%20love%2C%20eloping%20and%20having%20sexual%20intercourse%2C%20and%20subsequently%20attracting%20the%20provisions%20of%20the%20POCSO%20and%2For%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%2C%201860.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20was%20also%20asked%20by%20the%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20high%20court%20(Gwalior%20bench)%20to%20look%20into%20how%20the%20enforcement%20of%20the%20POCSO%20Act%2C%20in%20its%20present%20form%2C%20causes%20%E2%80%9Cgross%20injustice%20in%20cases%20of%20statutory%20rape%20where%20de%20facto%20consent%20is%20present%20from%20the%20girl%20child%20or%20where%20such%20a%20relationship%20has%20subsequently%20resulted%20in%20a%20marriage%2C%20with%20or%20without%20children.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20December%20last%20year%2C%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%20said%20that%20parliament%20must%20address%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Findia-news%2Flegislature-must-consider-concern-over-age-of-consent-under-pocso-cji-101670697533788.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Econcerns%20regarding%20the%20age%20of%20consent%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20under%20the%20POCSO%20Act%2C%20which%20criminalises%20consensual%20sexual%20activities%20for%20those%20under%20the%20age%20of%2018.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELater%20that%20month%2C%20in%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpqars.nic.in%2Fannex%2F258%2FAU1748.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ereply%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%2C%20Union%20minister%20for%20women%20and%20child%20development%20Smriti%20Irani%20said%20that%20the%20government%20is%20not%20considering%20any%20proposal%20to%20reduce%20the%20age%20of%20consent%20from%2018%20to%2016%20years.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20law%20commission%20report%20was%20prepared%20after%20looking%20at%20available%20judgments%2C%20and%20consultations%20with%20the%20National%20Commission%20for%20Protection%20of%20Child%20Rights%20(NCPCR)%2C%20former%20judges%2C%20lawyers%2C%20child%20rights%20activists%2C%20NGOs%20and%20academicians%2C%20responses%20from%20all%20the%20high%20courts%20and%20data%20from%20National%20Crime%20Records%20Bureau%20(NCRB).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F07%2F13150411%2FScreen-Shot-2020-07-13-at-3.00.03-PM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22842%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F07%2F13150411%2FScreen-Shot-2020-07-13-at-3.00.03-PM.png%20842w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F07%2F13150411%2FScreen-Shot-2020-07-13-at-3.00.03-PM-300x139.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-466479%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22391%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIllustration%3A%20The%20Wire%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EWhy%20commission%20said%20age%20of%20consent%20cannot%20be%20reduced%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20arguing%20against%20the%20automatic%20decriminalisation%20of%20consensual%20sexual%20acts%20by%20persons%20above%2016%20years%2C%20the%20commission%20said%20that%20consent%20can%20always%20be%20manufactured.%20It%20also%20said%20that%20if%20the%20police%20or%20investigating%20agencies%20are%20to%20determine%20whether%20there%20was%20consent%20or%20not%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20genuine%20cases%20under%20POCSO%20may%20not%20see%20trial%20on%20account%20of%20the%20agencies%20declaring%20them%20to%20be%20cases%20of%20consensual%20romantic%20sexual%20relationship.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CMoreover%2C%20it%20cannot%20be%20ignored%20that%20reducing%20the%20age%20of%20consent%20will%20have%20a%20direct%20and%20negative%20bearing%20on%20the%20fight%20against%20child%20marriage%20and%20child%20trafficking%2C%20the%20battles%20against%20which%20have%20been%20hard-fought%20and%20are%20still%20ongoing%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EArguing%20against%20carving%20out%20a%20limited%20exception%20for%20sexual%20relations%20with%20a%20child%20above%2016%20years%2C%20the%20commission%20said%20that%20the%20proposed%20solution%20is%20prone%20to%20misuse%20as%20the%20consent%20of%20a%20child%20is%20no%20consent%20and%20reading%20the%20same%20would%20be%20%E2%80%9Cdeeply%20problematic.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CAll%20children%20deserve%20the%20protection%20of%20the%20special%20law%20enacted%20for%20this%20very%20purpose%20and%20diluting%20the%20age%20of%20consent%20will%20deprive%20a%20significant%20portion%20of%20the%20child%20population%2C%20especially%20young%20girls%20aged%2016%20to%2018%20years%2C%20of%20the%20protection%20and%20expose%20them%20to%20unchecked%20exploitation.%20The%20increasing%20incidents%20of%20grooming%20and%20cyber-crimes%20such%20as%20sextortion%20are%20classic%20examples%20of%20how%20children%20in%20this%20vulnerable%20age%20group%20can%20be%20trapped%20and%20exploited%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHighlighting%20a%20submission%20from%20Vikram%20Srivastava%20of%20Independent%20Thought%2C%20the%20commission%20said%20that%20in%20Assam%20some%20parents%20arrange%20marriages%20between%20minors%20or%20a%20minor%20and%20an%20adult%20by%20signing%20notarised%20agreements%20stating%20that%20the%20minors%20or%20the%20minor%20and%20the%20adult%20have%20fallen%20in%20love.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThus%2C%20any%20reduction%20in%20the%20age%20of%20consent%20will%20inevitably%20provide%20a%20safe%20harbour%20provision%20to%20coerce%20minor%20girls%20into%20subjugation%2C%20marital%20rape%20and%20other%20forms%20of%20abuse%2C%20including%20trafficking%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EStating%20that%20while%20the%20age%20of%20consent%20and%20age%20of%20marriage%20should%20not%20be%20conflated%20in%20theory%2C%20in%20practice%2C%20given%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20social%20milieu%2C%20the%20two%20are%20intrinsically%20linked.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20many%20cases%20before%20the%20High%20Courts%2C%20one%20of%20the%20grounds%20for%20allowing%20bail%20or%20quashing%20the%20proceedings%20is%20that%20the%20victim%20and%20accused%20have%20got%20married%20and%2C%20in%20a%20number%20of%20cases%2C%20have%20a%20child%20as%20well.%20Thus%2C%20marriage%20and%20age%20of%20consent%20cannot%20be%20considered%20mutually%20exclusive%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20commission%20also%20said%20that%20if%20the%20age%20of%20consent%20and%20age%20of%20marriage%20are%20to%20be%20disassociated%2C%20then%20%E2%80%9Cconsent%20can%20always%20be%20pleaded%20to%20exist%20where%20the%20accused%20marries%20the%20victim%2C%20even%20if%20the%20said%20%E2%80%98consent%E2%80%99%20arises%20after%20the%20occurrence%20of%20the%20alleged%20offence.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThus%2C%20introducing%20the%20element%20of%20consent%20can%20provide%20an%20opportunity%20for%20child-abusers%20to%20escape%20the%20rigours%20of%20law%20and%20enjoy%20impunity%20by%20using%20loopholes%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20commission%20also%20highlighted%20an%20unpublished%20report%20of%20the%20Satyarthi%20Global%20Policy%20Institute%20for%20Children%2C%20Kailash%20Satyarthi%20Children%E2%80%99s%20Foundation%20(2022)%20on%20the%20prevalence%20and%20nature%20of%20child%20sexual%20abuse%20in%20India%20to%20state%20that%20victims%20themselves%20identify%20friends%20and%20boyfriend%2Fgirlfriend%20as%20the%20most%20common%20perpetrators%20of%20sexual%20abuse.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20very%20real%20possibility%20of%20young%20girls%20being%20easily%20seduced%20in%20love%20traps%20and%20then%20sold%20off%20in%20trafficking%20cannot%20and%20should%20not%20be%20ignored.%20Any%20element%20of%20consent%20can%20be%20misused%20and%20may%20lead%20to%20children%20being%20at%20the%20mercy%20of%20adult%20abusers%2C%20thereby%20enabling%20prostitution%20and%20exploitation%20of%20children.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EJudicial%20discretion%20in%20sentencing%20strikes%20%E2%80%98delicate%20balance%E2%80%99%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20commission%20said%20that%20the%20solution%20of%20introducing%20judicial%20discretion%20in%20sentencing%20seems%20to%20strike%20a%20%E2%80%9Cdelicate%20balance%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%20and%20protects%20children%20from%20sexual%20exploitation.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20cannot%20be%20any%20automatic%20decriminalisation%20of%20sexual%20acts%20with%20a%20person%20between%20the%20age%20of%201%206%20to%2018%20years%20and%20carving%20out%20a%20limited%20judicial%20discretion%20at%20the%20stage%20of%20sentencing%20is%20a%20more%20reasonable%20approach%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPutting%20the%20onus%20on%20the%20courts%2C%20the%20commission%20said%20that%20only%20a%20%E2%80%9Cjudicially%20trained%20mind%20aided%20by%20experts%20will%20be%20able%20to%20appropriately%20determine%20whether%20the%20consent%20in%20fact%20of%20the%20child%20in%20question%20was%20indeed%20free%20from%20any%20coercion%2C%20deception%2C%20fraud%20or%20undue%20influence.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20commission%20has%20accordingly%20recommended%20that%20such%20judicial%20discretion%20in%20reducing%20the%20minimum%20sentencing%20under%20the%20POCSO%20Act%20can%20be%20introduced%20if%20the%20age%20difference%20between%20the%20victim%20child%20and%20the%20accused%20is%20less%20than%20three%20years%20and%20when%20tacit%20approval%20is%20established.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20has%20also%20recommended%20that%20discretion%20be%20used%20if%20the%20accused%20has%20no%20criminal%20antecedents%2C%20bears%20good%20conduct%20after%20the%20offence%2C%20there%20is%20no%20element%20of%20undue%20force%2C%20coercion%2C%20or%20any%20element%20indicating%20child%20trafficking%3B%20and%20the%20child%20was%20not%20used%20for%20any%20pornographic%20purposes%2C%20among%20others.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fpocso-act-highest-pendency-uttar-pradesh-percentage%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Takes%201%20Year%2C%205%20Months%20to%20Dispose%20of%20a%20POCSO%20Case%3B%20UP%20Has%20Highest%20Pendency%20Percentage%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3E%E2%80%98Why%20is%20trafficking%20coming%20to%20muddy%20the%20waters%20of%20consent%20under%20POCSO%3F%E2%80%99%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EVidya%20Reddy%2C%20the%20executive%20director%20of%20Tulir%20%E2%80%93%20Centre%20for%20the%20Prevention%20%26amp%3B%20Healing%20of%20Child%20Sexual%20Abuse%2C%20who%20was%20consulted%20by%20the%20commission%20while%20preparing%20the%20report%2C%20said%20that%20the%20link%20between%20trafficking%20and%20not%20reducing%20the%20age%20of%20consent%20is%20not%20explained.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CTrafficking%20is%20being%20cited%20as%20one%20of%20the%20major%20reasons%20why%20they%20are%20not%20reducing%20the%20age%20(of%20consent).%20Even%20if%20that%20is%20the%20case%2C%20there%20should%20be%20evidence%20backed%20by%20scientific%20rigour%20to%20back%20that%20supposition.%20I%20would%20like%20to%20understand%20where%20is%20the%20evidence%20to%20show%20that%20there%20is%20a%20link%20between%20trafficking%20and%20being%20tricked%20to%20get%20married.%20In%20addition%2C%20POCSO%20is%20to%20deal%20with%20sexual%20offences.%20Even%20during%20the%20drafting%20of%20POCSO%2C%20the%20issue%20of%20trafficking%20came%20up%20and%20we%20decided%20that%20the%20IPC%20sections%20strongly%20deal%20with%20trafficking%2C%20whether%20it%20is%20an%20adult%20or%20a%20child%20because%20there%20is%20no%20question%20of%20consent%20in%20trafficking.%20So%20why%20is%20trafficking%20suddenly%20coming%20to%20muddy%20the%20waters%20of%20consent%20in%20POCSO%3F%E2%80%9D%20she%20said%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBharti%20Ali%2C%20co-founder%20and%20executive%20director%20of%20HAQ%3A%20Centre%20for%20Child%20Rights%2C%20said%20that%20exceptions%20could%20have%20been%20created%20for%20cases%20of%20trafficking.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CNobody%20is%20saying%20that%20trafficking%20should%20not%20be%20dealt%20with%20strictly.%20You%20could%20make%20those%20exceptions%20for%20cases%20of%20trafficking.%20Child%20trafficking%20is%20not%20only%20for%20prostitution.%20We%20have%20the%20IPC%20(Indian%20Penal%20Code)%20which%20recognises%20that%20children%20are%20trafficked%20for%20labour%2C%20slavery-like%20situations%2C%20adoption%20and%20myriad%20other%20purposes.%20We%20cannot%20blanketly%20say%20that%20all%20trafficking%20is%20for%20prostitution.%20Anyway%2C%20trafficking%20laws%20are%20very%20clear%20that%20there%20is%20no%20question%20of%20consent%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAli%20said%20that%20the%20age%20of%20sexual%20consent%20cannot%20be%20equated%20with%20the%20age%20of%20marriage%20in%20any%20way.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20had%20very%20clearly%20mentioned%20this%20in%20our%20submissions.%20It%20is%20also%20a%20way%20of%20controlling%20the%20sexuality%20of%20women%20and%20adolescent%20boys%20and%20girls.%20The%20whole%20approach%20is%20very%20protectionist%20and%20it%20is%20not%20about%20the%20safety%20of%20children.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F11%2F20150700%2Fimage-598.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F11%2F20150700%2Fimage-598.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F11%2F20150700%2Fimage-598-300x170.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F11%2F20150700%2Fimage-598-1024x581.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-629341%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22681%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ERepresentative%20image.%20Photo%3A%20Unsplash%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3E%E2%80%98Report%20ineffective%E2%80%99%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAmit%20Anand%20Tiwari%2C%20advocate%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20and%20the%20additional%20advocate%20general%20for%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20said%20that%20the%20commission%20has%20been%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20%E2%80%9Cineffective%20in%20answering%20the%20question%20it%20was%20supposed%20to%20address.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20report%20has%20been%20ineffective%20in%20resolving%20the%20issue%20posed%20before%20the%20commission%2C%20i.e.%2C%20genuine%20cases%20of%20the%20offender%20and%20the%20victim%2C%20both%20of%20a%20young%20and%20impressionable%20age%2C%20being%20in%20a%20consensual%20relationship.%20While%20being%20of%20the%20opinion%20that%20introducing%20the%20exception%20of%20consent%20would%20result%20in%20the%20same%20being%20misused%20and%20would%20negate%20the%20entire%20objective%20of%20the%20(POCSO)%20Act%2C%20the%20Commission%20has%20not%20taken%20into%20account%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20burden%20of%20proving%20such%20consent%20would%20have%20been%20on%20the%20accused%2C%20who%20would%20plead%20the%20same%20under%20Section%20105%20of%20the%20Indian%20Evidence%20Act%2C%201872%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20sentencing%20exception%20has%20been%20created%20without%20any%20guidelines.%20It%20does%20not%20provide%20for%20any%20quantum%20of%20sentence%2C%20and%20the%20same%20has%20been%20left%20entirely%20to%20the%20discretion%20of%20the%20judge%2C%20who%2C%20despite%20the%20presence%20of%20exceptional%20circumstances%2C%20may%20award%20the%20maximum%20sentence.%20Further%2C%20the%20Commission%20has%20overlooked%20the%20provisions%20of%20the%20Probation%20of%20Offenders%20Act%2C%201958%2C%E2%80%9D%20Tiwari%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20added%20that%20the%20Commission%20has%20failed%20to%20notice%20that%20merely%20providing%20discretion%20in%20awarding%20sentences%20will%20still%20retain%20the%20stigmatic%20effect%20of%20conviction%20for%20an%20offence%20relating%20to%20moral%20turpitude%2C%20which%20will%20be%20treated%20as%20a%20very%20severe%20stigma%20throughout%20the%20life%20of%20the%20person%20convicted.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBharat%20Chugh%2C%20Supreme%20Court%20advocate%20and%20former%20civil%20judge%2C%20said%20that%20while%20the%20recommendations%20are%20well-intentioned%2C%20they%20don%E2%80%99t%20go%20far%20enough.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CCertain%20cases%20of%20sexual%20experimentation%20between%20young%20people%20(with%20no%20indication%20of%20abuse%20of%20power%20or%20dominant%20position)%20should%20have%20been%20decriminalised%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20India%2C%20the%20process%20is%20more%20often%20than%20not%2C%20the%20punishment.%20Such%20criminal%20prosecutions%20(even%20if%20they%20don%E2%80%99t%20lead%20to%20jail%20but%20detention%20in%20the%20juvenile%20observation%20homes%20only)%20are%20punishment%20enough%20%E2%80%93%20by%20themselves.%20The%20power%20of%20the%20court%20to%20deal%20with%20such%20young%20accused%20with%20leniency%20is%20good%20and%20much%20better%20than%20the%20current%20system%2C%20but%20%5Bthe%20recommendation%5D%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20go%20far%20enough.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20added%20that%20in%20cases%20where%20the%20accused%20is%20just%20above%2018%20years%20old%20(and%20the%20victim%20girl%20just%20below%2018)%2C%20the%20offence%2C%20which%20is%20currently%20non-bailable%2C%20should%20have%20been%20made%20bailable%20in%20the%20absence%20of%20any%20proof%20of%20abuse%20of%20dominant%20position%20and%20involvement%20of%20older%20accused.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CAs%20a%20result%20of%20this%2C%20imagine%20a%20situation%20where%20a%20girl%20is%2017%20and%20the%20boy%20is%2018%20years%202%20months.%20If%20an%20FIR%20is%20registered%2C%20the%20boy%20is%20almost%20always%20arrested%20and%20has%20to%20seek%20bail.%20This%20also%20needs%20to%20be%20dealt%20with.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAli%20said%20that%20the%20criminalisation%20ultimately%20defeats%20the%20purpose%20of%20protecting%20children.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20understand%20that%20every%20child%20under%20the%20age%20of%2018%20needs%20to%20be%20protected%2C%20but%20you%20need%20to%20recognise%20the%20agency%20of%20children%20above%2016.%20Ultimately%2C%20the%20goal%20is%20to%20protect%20children%20but%20in%20the%20process%2C%20if%20you%20are%20criminalising%20them%2C%20it%20defeats%20the%20purpose%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696238982000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F02142709%2Fpexels-cottonbro-studio-4631064.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fexpert-view-law-commission-lowering-age-of-consent%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Experts%20and%20activists%20have%20raised%20concerns%20about%20the%20continued%20criminalisation%20of%20consensual%20sexual%20relations%20between%20teenagers.%20The%20commission's%20report%20is%20ineffective%20in%20answering%20the%20issues%20it%20was%20meant%20to%20address%2C%20they%20say.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fexpert-view-law-commission-lowering-age-of-consent%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Sagrada%20Familia%20nears%20completion%20as%20towers%20are%20crowned%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696238280000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F10%2F1600x900%2Fskynews-la-sagrada-familia_6305907.jpg%3F20231002101356%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fbarcelonas-sagrada-familia-nears-completion-as-towers-are-crowned-12974910%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22More%20than%20140%20years%20since%20work%20began%20on%20Barcelona's%20famous%20Sagrada%20Familia%20(The%20Holy%20Family)%20the%20city%20is%20celebrating%20a%20milestone%3A%20the%20completion%20of%20four%20of%20its%20towers.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2279%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fbarcelonas-sagrada-familia-nears-completion-as-towers-are-crowned-12974910%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fbarcelonas-sagrada-familia-nears-completion-as-towers-are-crowned-12974910%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fbarcelonas-sagrada-familia-nears-completion-as-towers-are-crowned-12974910%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Prasar%20Bharati%20Does%20Not%20Make%20Copyright%20Claims%20on%20Public%20Service%20Content%2C%20Say%20Officials%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2015%2F10%2Fprasar-bharati-hq.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Prasar%20Bharati%20said%20on%20October%201%20(Sunday)%20that%20it%20does%20not%20make%20copyright%20claims%20on%20public%20service%20content%2C%20including%20parliamentary%20proceedings.%20This%20statement%20came%20in%20response%20to%20allegations%20that%20it%20had%20sent%20copyright%20infringement%20notices%20to%20YouTubers%20regarding%20parliamentary%20proceedings.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EGurdeep%20Singh%20Sappal%2C%20a%20former%20chief%20executive%20officer%2Feditor%20of%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20TV%2C%20raised%20the%20issue%20and%20argued%20that%20parliamentary%20proceedings%20are%20national%20assets%20of%20historical%20value%20and%20should%20be%20freely%20accessible%2C%20not%20subject%20to%20copyright.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CPrasar%20Bharti%20has%20sent%20notices%20to%20YouTubers%20invoking%20copyright%20on%20it.%20This%20is%20wrong.%20Parliamentary%20proceedings%20are%20national%20assets%20of%20historical%20value.%20They%20are%20not%20a%20commercial%20product%20that%20can%20be%20used%20for%20profiteering%20under%20the%20garb%20of%20copyright.%20In%20fact%2C%20any%20attempt%20to%20limit%20the%20access%20to%20parliamentary%20proceedings%20amounts%20to%20censorship%20and%20is%20an%20infringement%20of%20the%20rights%20of%20citizens%20(to)%20be%20informed%20of%20the%20happenings%20in%20the%20Parliament%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Sappal.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAny%20part%20of%20parliamentary%20debate%20can%20only%20be%20restricted%20from%20public%20access%20by%20a%20specific%20order%20of%20the%20Chair%20only%2C%20using%20the%20powers%20vested%20in%20them%20to%20expunge%20parts%20of%20proceedings.%20When%20I%20had%20started%20RSTV%2C%20this%20issue%20was%20deliberated%20upon%20by%20the%20Content%20Advisory%20Committee%20of%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha.%20It%20was%20the%20unanimous%20decision%20that%20parliamentary%20proceedings%20have%20to%20be%20provided%20to%20anyone%20free%20of%20cost%2C%20to%20be%20used%20freely%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Prasar%20Bharati%20officials%20emphasised%20that%20they%20had%20never%20issued%20such%20copyright%20notices%2C%20and%20their%20public%20service-related%20content%20is%20copyright-free.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20officials%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fprasar-bharati-does-not-make-copyright-claims-on-public-service-content-say-officials%2Farticle67369734.ece%5C%22%3Etold%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20sometimes%20copyright%20violation%20notices%20might%20be%20automatically%20generated%20due%20to%20platform%20algorithms%2C%20but%20they%20encourage%20affected%20individuals%20to%20contest%20such%20notices%20to%20resolve%20the%20issue%20promptly.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20an%20official%20statement%20on%20this%20matter%20has%20not%20been%20released%20yet.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFollowing%20the%20report%2C%20Sappal%20posted%20on%20X%20(formerly%20Twitter)%3A%20%E2%80%9CThis%20statement%20attributed%20to%20Prasar%20Bharti%20officials%20would%20have%20been%20a%20welcome%20one%2C%20if%20only%20it%20were%20an%20official%20statement.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIf%20the%20intent%20of%20Prasar%20Bharti%20is%20indeed%20not%20to%20claim%20copyright%20over%20the%20usage%20of%20Parliamentary%20proceedings%2C%20then%20it%20must%20issue%20an%20official%20statement%20clarifying%20it.%20Such%20a%20statement%20can%20then%20be%20used%20by%20social%20media%20content%20creators%20for%20their%20official%20reply%20to%20the%20notices.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%20%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EThis%20statement%20attributed%20to%20Prasar%20Bharti%20officials%20would%20have%20been%20a%20welcome%20one%2C%20if%20only%20it%20were%20an%20official%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20intent%20of%20Prasar%20Bharti%20is%20indeed%20not%20to%20claim%20copyright%20over%20the%20usage%20of%20Parliamentary%20proceedings%2C%20then%20it%20must%20issue%20an%20official%20statement%E2%80%A6%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2Ftuz2sGYxvs%5C%22%3Ehttps%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2Ftuz2sGYxvs%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FbU3xgYPHFX%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2FbU3xgYPHFX%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%94%20Gurdeep%20Singh%20Sappal%20(%40gurdeepsappal)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fgurdeepsappal%2Fstatus%2F1708671318785450363%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EOctober%202%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1696236603000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2015%2F10%2Fprasar-bharati-hq.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Fprasar-bharati-does-not-make-copyright-claims-on-public-service-content-say-officials%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22However%2C%20an%20official%20statement%20on%20this%20matter%20has%20not%20been%20released%20yet.%22%2C%22