0%E2%80%98%3Cem%3ENari%20Shakti%20Vandan%20Adhiniyam%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%98%20was%20passed%20by%20the%20Indian%20Parliament%20last%20week%2C%20under%20which%2C%2033%20percent%20of%20seats%20in%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20state%20assemblies%20are%20promised%20to%20women.%20This%20landmark%20bill%20was%20passed%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20by%20an%20overwhelming%20majority%20of%20454-2%20votes.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EFirst%20tabled%20in%201996%2C%20it%20was%20one%20of%20the%20longest%20pending%20legislations%20in%20Parliament.%20It%20took%20eight%20different%20governments%2C%2027%20years%2C%20and%20a%20fight%20by%20women%20across%20the%20country%20to%20make%20this%20Bill%20a%20reality.%20Presently%2C%20there%20are%20102%20women%20parliamentarians%20out%20of%20a%20total%20of%20766%2C%20which%20accounts%20for%20only%2013%20percent.%20This%20Bill%20is%20much%20needed%2C%20as%20India%20ranks%20141%20in%20women%20representation%20in%20parliament%2C%20as%20per%20an%20Inter-Parliamentary%20Union%20(IPU)%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20historic%20bill%20is%20here%20today%20thanks%20to%20the%20efforts%20of%20many%20women%20politicians%20and%20activists%2C%20one%20of%20whom%20is%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F328785%2Fimportant-letters-from-nehru-gandhi-sigmund-freud-that-shaped-india-history%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPramila%20Dandavate%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20an%20MP%20from%20Mumbai%2C%20who%20had%20first%20introduced%20this%20Bill%20as%20a%20private%20member%E2%80%99s%20Bill%20in%20the%20early%201980s%2C%20in%20the%20seventh%20Lok%20Sabha.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20VP%20Singh%20government%20in%201989%2C%20she%20was%20the%20one%20who%20first%20demanded%2033%20percent%20reservation%20for%20women%20in%20the%20Parliament%20and%20Vidhan%20Sabha.%20This%20trailblazer%20started%20writing%20charters%20for%20women%E2%80%99s%20rights%20in%20the%201970s.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EThe%20women%20behind%20the%20victory%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20582px)%20100vw%2C%20582px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Fbill4-1695994589.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22582%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Pramila%20Dandavate%20at%20a%20meeting%20discussing%20the%20women's%20reservation%20bill.%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Fbill4-1695994589.jpg%20582w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Fbill4-1695994589-300x220.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Fbill4-1695994589-500x366.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Fbill4-1695994589-150x110.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-331342%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22426%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EPramila%20Dandavate%20at%20a%20meeting%20discussing%20the%20women%E2%80%99s%20reservation%20bill.%20Image%20courtesy%20CSR%20India%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%201987%2C%20former%20prime%20minister%20Rajiv%20Gandhi%20constituted%20a%20committee%20for%20the%20National%20Perspective%20Plan%20for%20Women.%20This%20committee%20was%20led%20by%20union%20minister%20Margaret%20Alva%20and%20proposed%20reservations%20in%20rural%20and%20local%20body%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20bill%20was%20drafted%20by%20this%20committee%20of%20women%20parliamentarians%20%E2%80%94%20including%20Alva%2C%20Geeta%20Mukherjee%2C%20Susheela%20Gopalan%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F214827%2Fvalentines-day-love-letters-emergency-madhu-pramila-dandavate-history-nor41%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EPramila%20Dandavate%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Dr%20Ranjana%20Kumari%2C%20who%20has%20also%20been%20fighting%20for%20the%20passage%20of%20the%20Bill%20for%20more%20than%20two%20decades%2C%20told%20%3Cem%3EFeminism%20in%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20website.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThey%20%5Bthese%20women%5D%20went%20around%20the%20country%20%5Band%5D%20sought%20opinions%20about%20the%20Bill%20and%20drafted%20it.%20I%20was%20one%20of%20the%20young%20scholars%20who%20helped%20in%20the%20process.%20It%20was%20their%20wisdom%2C%20and%20I%20put%20it%20in%20words.%20We%20eventually%20formed%20the%20%E2%80%98Seven%20Sisters%E2%80%99%2C%20where%20seven%20major%20national%20organisations%20of%20women%20came%20together%20and%20started%20campaigning%20for%20it%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20harbinger%20for%20change%20in%20women%E2%80%99s%20reservation%20were%20the%20local%20administrative%20bodies.%20In%201992%20and%201993%2C%20two%20bills%20were%20passed%2C%20which%20reserved%2033%20percent%20of%20seats%20and%20chairperson%20posts%20for%20women%20in%20rural%20and%20local%20body%20elections%20during%20PV%20Narasimha%20Rao%E2%80%99s%20tenure%20as%20prime%20minister.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Indian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%20report%20states%20that%20this%20has%20paved%20the%20way%20for%20the%20election%20of%20around%20one%20million%20women%20at%20village%2C%20block%20and%20district%20levels.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201600px)%20100vw%2C%201600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Fbill2-min-1695994429.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Women%20campaigning%20for%20reservation%20in%20Parliament.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Fbill2-min-1695994429.jpg%201600w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Fbill2-min-1695994429-300x169.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Fbill2-min-1695994429-500x281.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Fbill2-min-1695994429-768x432.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Fbill2-min-1695994429-1536x864.jpg%201536w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Fbill2-min-1695994429-150x84.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-331337%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EWomen%20campaigning%20for%20reservation%20in%20Parliament.%20Image%20courtesy%20CSR%20India%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20passage%20of%20these%20bills%20led%20to%20a%20push%20by%20activists%20like%20Pramila%20to%20expand%20the%20scope%20of%20the%20reservation%20to%20the%20lower%20house%20of%20parliament%20and%20state%20assemblies.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CReservation%20at%20the%20%3Cem%3Epanchayat%20%3C%2Fem%3Elevel%20has%20been%20a%20huge%20success.%20During%20the%201987%20elections%20in%20Karnataka%2C%2018%2C000%20women%20were%20elected%20to%20the%20various%20local%20government%20bodies%20after%20the%20JD-led%20government%20introduced%2025%20percent%20reservation%20for%20women%20in%20the%20%3Cem%3Epanchayats%3C%2Fem%3E.%20Women%20proved%20to%20be%20better%20representatives%20than%20men.%20I%20think%20that%20the%20quality%20of%20the%20Parliament%20will%20definitely%20improve%20as%20more%20women%20come%20in.%20In%20the%20past%2C%20women%E2%80%99s%20performance%20has%20been%20far%20better%20and%20they%20tend%20to%20be%20less%20corrupt%2C%E2%80%9D%20Pramila%20said%20in%20an%20interview%20with%20%3Cem%3EIndia%20Together%3C%2Fem%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EOn%2012%20September%201996%2C%20the%2081st%20Constitutional%20Amendment%20Bill%20was%20tabled%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20and%20sought%20to%20introduce%2033%20percent%20reservation%20for%20women.%20Multiple%20reports%20state%20that%20it%20was%20Pramila%20Dandavate%20who%20tabled%20this%20bill.%20The%20Bill%20was%20referred%20to%20a%20joint%20committee%20which%20submitted%20a%20recommendation%20in%20December%201996.%20However%2C%20it%20lapsed%20after%20the%20dissolution%20of%20the%20H%20D%20Deve%20Gowda%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20then%20tabled%20in%201997%20under%20the%20I%20K%20Gujral%20government%2C%20but%20lapsed%20again%2C%20and%20was%20introduced%20in%201998%2C%201999%2C%202002%2C%20and%202003%20during%20the%20NDA%20government%2C%20but%20lapsed%20each%20time.%20There%20was%20some%20progress%20in%202008%20during%20the%20Manmohan%20Singh-led%20UPA%20government.%20The%20Bill%20was%20introduced%20in%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha.%20It%20was%20passed%20in%20the%20Upper%20House%20in%202010.%20It%20finally%20saw%20the%20light%20of%20day%20on%2019%20September%202023%2C%20as%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20passed%20it%20under%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Women%20are%20creators%E2%80%99%3C%2Fh2%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201600px)%20100vw%2C%201600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Fbill3-min-1695994427.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22PM%20with%20women%20MPs%20after%20the%20Bill%20was%20passed.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Fbill3-min-1695994427.jpg%201600w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Fbill3-min-1695994427-300x132.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Fbill3-min-1695994427-500x219.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Fbill3-min-1695994427-768x337.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Fbill3-min-1695994427-1536x674.jpg%201536w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Fbill3-min-1695994427-150x66.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-331336%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22702%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EPM%20Modi%20with%20women%20MPs%20after%20the%20Bill%20was%20passed%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EMost%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F329325%2Fwomen-in-history-icons-of-india-neerja-bhanot-rajkumari-gupta-sitara-begum-gangubai-hangal%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewomen%20activists%20and%20leaders%20%3C%2Fa%3Ehave%20said%20over%20the%20years%20that%20it%20was%20patriarchal%20thinking%20that%20was%20the%20biggest%20opposition%20to%20this%20Bill.%20In%20fact%2C%20several%20women%20leaders%20across%20the%20political%20spectrum%20realised%20the%20need%20for%20reservation%20only%20after%20coming%20into%20positions%20of%20power.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CUntil%201975-76%2C%20I%20was%20in%20favour%20of%20reservation%20for%20women%20only%20up%20to%20the%20local%20and%20%3Cem%3Ezilla%20parishad%3C%2Fem%3E%20levels.%20When%20the%20Janata%20Dal%20came%20to%20power%2C%20women%20were%20given%20very%20few%20tickets%20even%20though%20they%20had%20participated%20in%20the%20struggle%20for%20democracy%20under%20Jaiprakash%20Narayan.%20Since%20then%2C%20I%20have%20become%20a%20consistent%20supporter%20of%20reservation%20for%20women%2C%20including%20in%20the%20Parliament.%20I%20feel%20that%20our%20party%20wants%20women%20to%20be%20decorative%20pieces%2C%20like%20%3Cem%3Eachar%20%3C%2Fem%3E(pickle)%20with%20food%20or%20a%20flower%20pot.%20They%20do%20not%20want%20to%20share%20power%20in%20the%20real%20sense%20of%20the%20word%2C%E2%80%9D%20Pramila%20told%20%3Cem%3EIndia%20Together%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBJP%20leader%20Uma%20Bharti%20said%20to%20the%20same%20publication%2C%20%E2%80%9CIn%20principle%2C%20I%20am%20against%20reservation%20because%20I%20believe%20that%20women%20should%20come%20forward%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20their%20own%20merit%20and%20hard%20work.%20But%20my%2012%20years%20of%20experience%20in%20politics%20have%20led%20me%20to%20believe%20that%20this%20does%20not%20happen.%20Women%20rarely%20manage%20to%20come%20forward%20and%20when%20they%20try%20to%20do%20so%2C%20their%20own%20colleagues%20brand%20them%20as%20loose-characters.%20Therefore%2C%20I%20believe%20that%20women%20will%20come%20into%20politics%20only%20if%20a%20reservation%20policy%20is%20implemented.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPramila%20joined%20hands%20with%20women%20across%20political%20parties%20to%20make%20this%20Bill%20a%20reality.%20She%20worked%20with%20Geeta%20Mukherjee%2C%20Mamata%20Banerjee%2C%20Meira%20Kumar%2C%20Sumitra%20Mahajan%2C%20Sushma%20Swaraj%2C%20Uma%20Bharti%2C%20and%20Hannan%20Mollah%2C%20among%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%20%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20610px)%20100vw%2C%20610px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Fwomens-bill-1695994430.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Leaders%20from%20different%20political%20parties%20celebrating%20passage%20of%20the%20women's%20reservation%20bill%20in%202010.%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22610%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Fwomens-bill-1695994430.jpg%20610w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Fwomens-bill-1695994430-300x169.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Fwomens-bill-1695994430-500x281.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2Fwomens-bill-1695994430-150x84.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-331338%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22343%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ESushma%20Swaraj%2C%20Brinda%20Karat%2C%20and%20Najma%20Heptulla%20celebrating%20the%20passage%20of%20the%20bill%20in%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20in%202010%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%20%3Cp%3EThey%20travelled%20across%20the%20country%20to%20assess%20the%20ground%20realities.%20This%20committee%2C%20led%20by%20Mukherjee%2C%20made%20seven%20recommendations%2C%20which%20included%20reservation%20for%20a%20period%20of%2015%20years%2C%20and%20sub-reservation%20of%20Anglo-Indians.%20Five%20of%20these%20recommendations%20have%20been%20made%20a%20reality%20today.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPramila%20also%20worked%20tirelessly%20to%20amend%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F315357%2Fmanilal-doctor-revolutionary-leader-freed-indentured-indian-labourers-in-fiji-mauritius%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAnti-dowry%20and%20Sati%20Prevention%20Acts%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20highlighting%20her%20dedication%20to%20women%E2%80%99s%20rights.%20She%20campaigned%20against%20dowry%20killings%20and%20the%20practice%20of%20%3Cem%3ESati%3C%2Fem%3E%20(where%20a%20widow%20would%20end%20her%20life%20by%20jumping%20into%20her%20husband%E2%80%99s%20pyre)%20and%20was%20instrumental%20in%20bringing%20about%20the%20Amendment%20to%20the%20Dowry%20Prohibition%20Act%20and%20the%20Sati%20Prohibition%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHer%20political%20activism%20led%20to%20her%2018-month%20imprisonment%20during%20the%20Emergency.%20She%20established%20the%20Mahila%20Dakshata%20Samiti%20and%20co-authored%20%E2%80%9CWidows%2C%20Abandoned%20and%20Destitute%20Women%20in%20India%E2%80%9D%20with%20Jamila%20Verghese%20and%20Dr%20Kumari.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20she%20died%20on%2031%20December%202001%2C%20much%20before%20she%20could%20realise%20the%20fruits%20of%20her%20efforts.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20legislation%20will%20bear%20fruit%20only%20in%202029%2C%20thanks%20to%20a%20delimitation%20clause%20in%20the%20bill.%20The%20reservation%20is%20proposed%20to%20be%20implemented%20after%20a%20new%20census%20is%20published%20and%20the%20delimitation%20exercise%20is%20completed.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThis%20